Commentary.Commentary: The Australian inning is all set to begin! 29 overs are left in the day and it will be interesting to see how both teams approach this phase of the game. Have to say, it can turn out to be quite a crucial passage of play. The Sri Lankan players now make their way out to the middle. David Warner and Usman Khawaja are the openers for Australia. Asitha Fernando has a brand new ball in his hand. Let's play...
... Second Innings ...

Sri Lanka though have a decent score on the board now. It may not look big on paper but taking into consideration the pitch and loads of spin bowling options that Sri Lanka have, it will not be an easy task for the Aussies. It will be a big test for Australia but they will take confidence from their batting success under similar conditions in Pakistan. Can they pass the trial by spin here? We shall find out soon. Stay tuned.

A quick wrap to the Lankan innings after Tea! Nathan Lyon broke the dangerous-looking partnership between Ramesh Mendis and Dickwella in his first over of the evening session. Dickwella too could not add much after the break and departed after playing a handy knock of 58 for his team. Lyon eventually finished with his 20th Test fifer while Swepson took three wickets and overall, Australia would be pretty happy with their bowling performance.

OUT! Vandersay holes out! Floated delivery, landing full around leg and spinning away, Jeffrey Vandersay sits down on one knee and tries to slog it across the line. It comes from the top half of his blade and it's a simple catch for Mitchell Starc at deep mid-wicket. Sri Lanka are all out for 212.
Commentary.Howout: c Mitchell Starc b Mitchell Swepson

Commentary.Commentary: Skidding down, from around leg, Jeffrey Vandersay tries to flick but misses.
Quicker and shorter on off, Vandersay punches from the back foot to covers.
Again it's short and around off, turning away, Jeffrey Vandersay steps back and then tries to reach out for his square cut but misses.
FOUR! Useful runs for Sri Lanka! Short delivery, around middle, Jeffrey Vandersay stands back and reverse-pulls it past the diving point fielder for a boundary.
Fuller and around off, driven back to the bowler.
Mitchell Swepson is back on. Can he finish things off in this over?

Aerial but it loops over leg gully. Turn and bounce again, from around off, Asitha Fernando tries to defend but gets an inside edge. It deflects off his pads and balloons behind Warner. They get two runs.
Asitha Fernando is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! The Flying Khawaja! What a screamer from him and Nathan Lyon has a fifer. Full and floated, around middle, Lasith Embuldeniya advances down the track and flicks it aerially towards mid-wicket. Usman Khawaja is manning that region, he shuffles across to his left a bit and then flies full stretch to catch it with both hands. Superbly done and now Australia are only one wicket away from closing the Sri Lankan innings.
Commentary.Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Flatter and shorter, around off, it's defended off the back foot.
Plays the reverse sweep again, this time wide of point and they cross for a single.

Edged but short! Flighted and around off, turning in, Jeffrey Vandersay tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and falls wide of Marnus Labuschagne at short leg. He stretches his left hand out but it drops away.
Fuller and on off, Jeffrey Vandersay also has the confidence to play the reverse sweep, connects decently but finds backward point.
Slightly short in length and on off, angling away, Lasith Embuldeniya allows it through to the keeper.
Fuller in length, on middle at 134 kph, Jeffrey Vandersay uses the angle and works it behind square leg for a single.
Targets the off stump with a length ball, Jeffrey Vandersay once again is solid in his defense off the back foot.
Full and outside off, angling in, Vandersay pushes it off the front foot to covers.
Fraction short and on off, Jeffrey Vandersay gets squared up on the back foot as he defends it to the off side.
Angles in a length ball around off, Jeffrey Vandersay defends it from the back foot.
Flatter and quicker, around off, Lasith defends it down from the back foot.

SIX! This one has gone all the way! 200 comes up. Fuller and around off, this time Lasith Embuldeniya goes down on one knee and smokes it over mid-wicket for a maximum. Niroshan Dickwella has shown the way, that's the way to bat on this track.
Beauty! Loopy and around off, drifting in and spinning away, Lasith Embuldeniya tries to defend off the front foot but misses.
Lasith Embuldeniya walks out next.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That's all from Niroshan Dickwella with the bat in this innings. Tossed up, full and around off, spinning away sharply, Dickwella goes down to sweep across the line but gets a faint  edge to the keeper. A good reflex catch from Alex Carey and Niroshan's adventurous batting comes to an end. The replays show that it came off the toe end of the bat.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Aerial but safe! Floated and full, around off, once again Dickwella tries to play the reverse-batted sweep but it takes his gloves and flies wide of first slip and backward point.
Fuller and around leg, Niroshan reverse-sweeps it firmly but finds the cover fielder.
Fraction short and on off, Dickwella defends it from the back foot.

FOUR! Switch on the T20 mode. We have already seen reverse sweep, paddle sweep, conventional sweep, and now Niroshan Dickwella pulls out the paddle scoop. Full and around off, angling in, Niroshan Dickwella goes down and spoons it behind the keeper for a boundary. As a result of that shot, Steven Smith is now placed at long stop. Interesting.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it gently, again towards mid off.
Fullish and around off, pushed to mid off.
Fuller in length and angling in around middle at 131 kph, Dickwella pushes it down with a straight bat to mid on.
Lands it on a good length and outside off, Dickwella pushes it from the back foot to covers.

Shout for an lbw again, the umpire turns it down. This time definitely it's too high. Turn and bounce from around off, Jeffrey Vandersay hangs back to defend but misses and is hit high on the pads. Would have been the umpire's call had Australia reviewed. It's clipping the top of the middle stump, shows the Ball Tracking. Anyway, a successful over for Lyon.
Jeffrey Vandersay walks out to the middle on his debut.

OUT! LBW! Tossed up, landing a touch short around off and turning back in sharply. Mendis goes back inside the crease to play at it but misses and is pinged on the back leg. They appeal but the umpire doesn't agree. Cummins has a word with his players and then takes the DRS. The Ball Tracking shows that it's hitting the stumps. A good review, the bounce didn't play a part. No bat too. Mendis returns but he was involved in an excellent partnership with Dickwella.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Huge shout for an lbw, not given! Looks to be high and it's spinning in too much as well. Anyway, Pat Cummins has decided to review. There is no bat involved as confirmed by UltraEdge! The Ball Tracking rolls and it shows that the impact is in line and the ball is hitting the stumps. So, the decision will be overturned. Ramesh Mendis has to walk back.
Spinning back in from around off, short in length, Mendis goes deep inside the crease and pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted and full, around middle, it's swept along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
Lyon switches to over the wicket and delivers a full ball around off, Dickwella presses forward and defends.
Loopy and full, around leg, Dickwella sweeps but finds short fine leg.
Nathan Lyon starts from the other end. So Australia, as expected, are starting with the combo of pace and spin after Tea.
Another defensive shot off the front foot to cap off this over.
Fuller in length and outside off, Mendis drives it from the bottom end of his bat to mid off.
Delivers it on a fuller length outside off, Mendis is on the front foot and pushes it to mid off.
A touch short in length and outside off, at 132 kph, Ramesh plays it down to point.
Around off, on a good length, Mendis taps it down to point and looks for a run. He is sent back.
Cummins begins from 'round the wicket and delivers a length ball on middle and leg, Niroshan Dickwella tickles it down to fine leg and takes a single.

We are back for the final session! The Australian players make their way out to the middle. Niroshan Dickwella and Ramesh Mendis also walk out to resume their innings. It will be the skipper, Pat Cummins to start the proceedings with the ball. Here we go...
… DAY 1, SESSION 3 …

Runs - 123, Wickets - 4! End of another engrossing session of Test cricket. Spin was always going to play a big part in this Test match and the Australian spinners, after not taking any wickets in the first session, managed to bag four in the afternoon. Two wickets each for Mitchell Swepson and Nathan Lyon but have to say, the knock from Dickwella has also kept Sri Lanka going on this tricky pitch. Other batters though could not do much in this middle session as just surviving on this pitch looks very tough. Ramesh Mendis has taken a leaf out of Dickwella’s book and they have stitched together an unbeaten 52-run stand. How many more can Sri Lanka score? Find out in the final session that begins at 3 pm IST (9.30 am GMT).
Angling away from the batter, on a length and outside off at 138 kph, Mendis covers his stumps and shoulders arms. That will be TEA on Day 1.
Spears it in, very full and around off at 140 clicks, Mendis clips it wide of mid on and scampers back for the second run.
Slower one at 129 kph, very full and outside off, Niroshan Dickwella pushes it to covers and picks up a single.
Gets behind the fuller delivery and pushes it defensively to mid on.
Slightly short and on off, Niroshan Dickwella works it from the back foot to mid-wicket.
On a length around off, defended.

FOUR BYES!  Wrong 'un goes wrong for the bowler. He serves it around leg and it turns down. Mendis fails to flick and the keeper fails to collect. Bonus runs as the ball crosses the fence at fine leg.

FIFTY FOR DICKWELLA! His 21st in Tests and second against Australia. Flighted and full, around middle, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it through square leg for a single.  It has been a great counter-attacking knock from him.
FOUR! Smacked! Swepson delivers it full and around middle, Dickwella reverse-sweeps it against the spin and nails it through cover-point. Moves to 49!
Short around off, turning away, Mendis goes back and forces it to sweeper cover for a run.
Full and floated, around off, Mendis defends it off his front foot.
Loopy and full, around leg, it's clipped to mid-wicket.
Lands on a length, outside off. Niroshan Dickwella drives it to the right of the mid off fielder and decides against taking the single.
Starc alters his length and goes back to the fuller length on off. Mendis works it to mid on for a single.
Pulls his length back and it is around off. Mendis defends it solidly towards the off side.
Starc goes fuller again on middle. Ramesh Mendis defends it back to the bowler.

A fullish delivery on off. Niroshan Dickwella drives it through covers. Usman Khawaja runs behind it and makes a good stop near the fence with a slide. Keeps it inside the fence as the batters run three.
On a good length, outside off. Niroshan Dickwella slashes it away from his body but misses.
Mitchell Starc returns to bowl before Tea. 1 for 24 in his 7 overs so far. Can he get the ball to reverse?
Leans forward and helps it towards mid-wicket. The bowler puts a slide but then lets it go to mid on.
FOUR! Shot! The delivery is short and outside off, Ramesh Mendis jumps back inside the crease and punches it down to long on for a boundary.
Floated and full, around off, it's defended off the front foot.
Perfect delivery! This is tossed up, around off. The ball pitches and turns away sharply to beat the front-foot defence of Ramesh Mendis.
On the shorter side on middle. Mendis works it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely played! Mitchell Swepson keeps it short and flatter outside off. Mendis goes back and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Goes flatter and quicker on off. Niroshan Dickwella defends it towards the off side off the front foot.

NOT OUT! It's missing the stumps and Australia lose another review. In total FIVE LEG BYES get added to the Lankan score. Flighted delivery, full and around leg, Mendis tries to flick but misses. He is thudded on the pads and the ball deflects to covers. There is a big chorus for the lbw appeal as the batters attempt to steal a run. The fielder attacks the ball and scores a direct hit at the bowler's end. The ball deflects, beats the mid on fielder and goes to the fence. Pat Cummins is surrounded by his teammates and with two seconds left on the timer, he takes the DRS. The bat is quite far away from the ball, so there is no need to check the UltraEdge and the Ball Tracking, as informed earlier, shows that it's missing the stumps.
A huge extended appeal for an lbw but the finger stays down. With two seconds left on the timer, Pat Cummins takes the review...
Lyon goes fuller again on leg. Niroshan Dickwella with another sweep shot to deep square leg for a single.
This is fuller and around off. Mendis sweeps it to fine leg for a single. Sweeps and reverse-sweeps all around us now!
Lyon stays with that middle and leg line. Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Angling into leg. Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it to short fine leg.
Swepson tosses it up on middle, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it to Marnus Labuschagne at short leg. The ball deflects as it hits his body and a single is taken.
The reverse-sweep saga continues! Attempted wrong 'un around leg. Niroshan Dickwella takes it on the full and reverse-sweeps it in front of square on the off side for a couple.
A tossed up delivery on middle, Mendis works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Again the reverse sweep! This is full on off. Niroshan Dickwella sends it to deep point for a single.
A flatter and shorter delivery on off. Niroshan Dickwella is right behind it to block it.
Fuller delivery, around off. Niroshan Dickwella looks to reverse-sweep it but the ball hits his pads and goes towards short leg.
On the shorter side. Turning into middle. Mendis blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Good shot! Same line from Lyon probably a bit fuller and Mendis sweeps it nicely towards the square leg fence.
Lot of excitement out there for the Aussie players as another ball hits the pads. Lyon pitches it around off and it turns in. Mendis tries to defend but gets hit high on his pads.
This is fuller outside off. Mendis goes for the sweep shot but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards the off side.
Tad shorter on off. Niroshan Dickwella punches it to covers for a single.
Lyon delivers it on off. Niroshan Dickwella gets across and looks to sweep but misses. The ball hits his pads but the impact seems outside off.
Shorter and a googly this time on middle. Mendis blocks it off the back foot,
Tossed up on middle. Niroshan Dickwella goes for the reverse sweep but gets the bottom of his blade. The ball rolls towards the off side and a single is taken.
Tossed up on off. Niroshan Dickwella blocks it out.
A flipper on middle and leg. Mendis tries to sweep it but only manages to get a faint glove on it. The ball hits his pads and rolls behind the keeper. A single taken. An appeal but nothing serious.
Drifting on leg. Mendis defends it towards the leg side. He looks for a single but Dickwella sends him back.
Fuller delivery, outside off. Niroshan Dickwella drives it through covers. Starc chases it and keeps it inside the fence with a slide. Three runs more added to the total. Good save from Starc!
Shorter length, turning into middle, Mendis goes deep in his crease and punches it through covers for a couple.
Goes fuller on off, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
On the shorter side turning into middle, Mendis goes back and works it past Warner at leg slip for a single.
Tossed up on off. Mendis skips down the track and defends it.
Extra bounce and turn again! Pitches it outside off and the ball turns in with plenty of good bounce to beat the outside edge of the batter's blade as he looks to push it towards the off side.
Ramesh Mendis is in next.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nathan Lyon strikes and this is another big wicket for Australia! Nathan Lyon keeps it a touch short and it turns into Mathews from around off. He goes deep in his crease and tries to work it towards the leg side. However, he does not control it completely and ends up hitting it to the left of Warner at leg gully. Another sharp catch is taken and Sri Lanka's ex-skipper is on his bike.
Commentary.Howout: c David Warner b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Pulls the length back on middle. Niroshan Dickwella skips down the track and defends it somehow onto the pitch.

A loud appeal from Carey but the umpire is not interested! This is fuller in length on middle. Niroshan Dickwella gets across a bit and sweeps it fine. The ball runs towards the fine leg fence and two runs are taken. Clearly, the bat is involved there and Cummins does well to not take a review. The umpire also waited for him to take the call. No signal from him till then. Anyway, it was away from the pads.
Googly that pitches on middle and turns in. Angelo Mathews goes back and works it to fine leg for a single.
Goes flatter and quicker on off. Niroshan Dickwella reverse-sweeps it to deep point for a single. This is the highest partnership of the innings so far, 39 to be precise!
This is full on the pads. Angelo Mathews flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
A flatter delivery on off. Niroshan Dickwella with a solid block off the front foot. He takes a single as the ball rolls towards the vacant cover region.
On the shorter side, on off. Niroshan Dickwella goes deep in his crease and pushes it to covers for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Angelo Mathews with a sweep shot now to fine leg for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Slightly shorter and Angelo Mathews works it towards the leg side off the back foot.
Now a conventional sweep. This is fuller angling into leg. Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! Niroshan Dickwella with another aggressive shot! This is full on middle. Niroshan Dickwella brings out the reverse sweep and hits it through cover-point for a boundary.
Tossed up, outside off. Angelo Mathews skips down the track and works it away to long on for a single.
Goes on the back foot and cuts a short ball through point for a single.
Lunges to a full ball and defends it back.
Shortish and around off, Mathews goes back to cut but chops it down on one bounce to Warner at second slip.
Shorter and outside off. Angelo Mathews goes back and pushes it towards point.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out to covers.
FOUR! Short in length around middle, a rare bad delivery by Swepson, Mathews rocks back and smashes it to the deep mid-wicket fence.

DRINKS! A productive hour of play for the visitors! They have taken three wickets and are on the top now with both spinners bowling effectively. However, Sri Lankan batters have adopted a positive approach with the bat and have scored 52 runs in the first hour. This is probably the way forward on this pitch which is showing all sorts of tricks. Niroshan Dickwella has played some aggresive shots but he has to make sure that he stays with Angelo Mathews who is looking solid out there.
FOUR! Dickwella is attacking Lyon here. Takes 14 from this over. Loopy and full, around off, Niroshan Dickwella kneels and muscles his slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Timed brilliantly by Dickwella. Very full and around middle, Niroshan Dickwella shows the full face of the bat and caresses it through mid on for a gorgeous boundary.
Fuller and around off, Dickwella sweeps it all along the ground through square leg. Glenn Maxwell (sub) runs across to his right in the deep and stops the ball. They take two runs.
Short in length and outside off, Niroshan Dickwella goes back and cuts but finds the point fielder.
A teasing delivery, loopy and full outside off, ND drives but finds mid off.
FOUR! Connects and connects well. Niroshan will go for his shots. Loopy and full, around off, Dickwella kneels down and powers it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Very full this time, around middle, Mathews drives it back to the bowler.
Loopy and around leg, turning away a bit, Mathews steps back and defends it down with gentle hands.
A touch flatter and around middle, Dickwella flicks it past the diving leg gully fielder for a single.
Drifting on the pads, fuller in length, Angelo wrists it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted and full, around off and spinning away, Mathews presses forward, covers the spin and defends it down.
Quicker through the air, a touch short around off and it's a flipper. Mathews hangs on the back foot and defends it at the last moment.
Fullish and around middle, Niroshan Dickwella drives it down the ground but finds Travis Head at mid off.
Play and a miss! Full and around off, turning away, Dickwella tries to play the slog sweep but misses.
Perfect delivery. Enough revs on the ball, gets it to drift around off and it spins away after landing. Dickwella tries to defend but misses.
Dickwella is out there to sweep everything. Loopy and full, outside off and spinning away, Niroshan fails to connect this time.
Quicker through the air, at 90 kph, too full and around off, Dickwella paddle sweeps it down to fine leg for a couple.
Floated delivery, Mathews goes down and fetches it from outside off as he sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Shortish and around off, Mathews punches it down to long off for a single. End of a terrific over from Swepson!
A conventional sweep this time, sending the full ball down to fine leg for a run. 100 comes up for Sri Lanka!
Dickwella opens his account with two runs. Fuller around off, it's reverse-swept past first slip for a couple.
No hat-trick! Full and flighted, around off, Dickwella sweeps and it goes on bounce to the fielder in front of square leg.
Niroshan Dickwella walks out to face the hat-trick ball!

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Chandimal bags a golden duck. And what a catch at second slip by David Warner. Beauty from Swepson again. Lovely drift on this delivery. It lands on a fuller length around leg and turns away. Dinesh Chandimal tries to defend but gets an outside edge. It perhaps brushes the gloves of Alex Carey before going to Warner at second slip. He shows great reflexes to go for the catch, and juggles as he falls down flat on the ground but somehow manages to stick it with his right arm near his chest. Steven Smith was also there in the vicinity, trying to help his mate but it was cleanly done by then. Australia on top!
Commentary.Howout: c David Warner b Mitchell Swepson

Commentary.Commentary: Dinesh Chandimal walks out at number 6.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHND! That's a good sharp catch by Alex Carey. Mitchell Swepson comes up with a brilliant delivery, something that leg spinners dream of! He gives this one some extra toss at 87 kph. The ball lands on a fuller length around middle. It grips and then spins away a bit as Dhananjaya de Silva tries to lean forward and defend. He misses and it kisses the outside edge on its way to the keeper. Mitchell Swepson is elated. It's been a great afternoon session for the Kangaroos. Nothing that Dhananjaya de Silva did wrong there, that was an unplayable delivery and would have got most batters out.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Swepson

Commentary.Commentary: Loopy and full, on middle, Mathews defends it with the turn by taking his bottom hand off the handle.

In the air... Dhananjaya de Silva is living dangerously. Flighted delivery, full and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva advances down the track for a big heave across the line. But it takes the toe end of his bat and flies through the gap between short mid-wicket and mid on. It goes in the deep and they collect a single.
Shortish and around middle, Mathews gets back and taps it past Warner at leg gully for a single.
Goes on the back foot and helps it wide of short leg for a single.

FOUR! Floated off spinner, landing around middle and spinning down, Dhananjaya de Silva gets a fine tickle behind his attempt flick. David Warner, at leg gully, initially looks to move to his left and gets wrong-footed as the ball races past his right side. It finds the fence at fine leg.
Oohhh... that missed the off pole by a whisker. Fuller in length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva tries to slog it over the leg side but misses.
Swepson goes short, around off, Mathews moves back and punches it to covers.
Silly point comes in.
Nice drift into the right-hander. It's full and spinning away from around leg. Mathews defends it from the outer half of his blade.
Shorter this time, around off, Mathews goes back and plays it down to covers.
Flighted and full, around leg, it's blocked back.
Tossed up, outside off, Mathews leaves.
Edgy! Loopy and full, around leg, de Silva tries to flick without accounting for the leg break. It takes the leading edge and rolls through cover-point for a run.
Spin from both ends now. Mitchell Swepson is back into the attack. Three overs for 9 runs so far.
Aerial but in the gap. Fuller and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva skips down the track and flicks it off the inner half of his blade. It's uppish but wide of mid-wicket and they cross for a run.
FOUR! Nicely played! Nathan Lyon drops it short and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes deep inside the crease and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary, his first.
Uses his feet again and this time works a full ball through mid-wicket for a single.
Too full in length, around off, Mathews plays the conventional sweep, not from the middle of the bat though. It goes straight to Warner at leg gully. Mathews falls while getting up.
Advances down the track to a full ball and defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! That's one way to deal with the spinning deliveries. Loopy and full, landing around leg, Angelo Mathews brings out the reverse-batted sweep and sends it past the left side of the backward point fielder for a boundary.
Fullish and around middle, angling in, Dhananjaya de Silva tries to flick but it takes the leading edge. Luckily for him, the ball drops short of the short extra cover fielder.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
In the channel around off, on a length, defended from the back foot to the off side.
Around midlde, on a length, de Silva wrists it to square leg.
Fuller again, around off, Dhananjaya de Silva drives but this time the bowler makes a fine stop in his followthrough.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.

Uppish but safe! Spinning in sharply, from around off, Mathews tries to defend but it takes the inner half and goes just wide of the outstretched right hand of Marnus Labuschagne at short leg fielder. Probing over!
Spinning in, around middle and leg, it's worked behind square leg for a single.

Dropped? Too tough to be honest. Plenty of inward spin on this one, jumping extra as well. It's tossed up around off, a puff of dust comes off as the ball lands. Dhananjaya de Silva tries to defend but it takes a thick inside edge and strikes him on the pads. The ball lobs in the air, Alex Carey's weight is on the left leg as he attempts to take the catch by stretching his right hand out. He fails to grab it cleanly.
Flatter and a touch shorter, around off and spinning in, de Silva defends it from the back foot.
Jumps down the track to a full ball and flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, full and outside off, Dhananjaya tries to drive through covers but it takes the inner portion and rolls back to the bowler.
Angles in a length ball around off, Angelo solidly defends it to the off side.
On a good length, around off, defended from the back foot.

Misunderstanding but no harm is done. Full and around off, Mathews pushes it away from the outer half of his bat to covers. Angelo takes a few steps forward and Dhananjaya de Silva comes charging down the track in response. Mathews sends him back and de Silva reaches in time as the fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end.
Fullish and angling in, around off, Mathews leans across and pushes it softly to mid on.
Around off, on a length, Mathews defends it from the back foot to covers.
Back of a length, around leg and jumping onto the batter, Mathews flicks it aerially but wide of short leg. They take two runs.
Pulls his length back, on middle. Angelo Mathews uses the depth of the crease and nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Uses his feet and gets to the pitch of the ball to work it away to long on for a single.
Flatter and slightly shorter on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva works it towards mid-wicket.
A tossed up delivery on off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward to defend it.
Dhananjaya de Silva walks in next.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a stunner by David Warner! This is a big wicket of the Lankan skipper and Nathan Lyon strikes early after Lunch! Nice loopy delivery, fuller in length and on middle. It's the arm ball. Dimuth Karunaratne gets forward to defend it. However, he gets a big inside edge onto his pads. The ball loops up in the air in front of second slip and David Warner dives forward to take a one-handed stunner. They appeal but the umpire takes it upstairs to confirm whether the catch is clean or not. The replays confirm that it is a clean catch and Dimuth Karunaratne walks back disappointed. Later on, the replays show that all the close-in fielders were appealing for lbw and it was only David Warner who realized that there was a catching opportunity. Smiles all around in the Aussie camp.
Commentary.Howout: c David Warner b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Is that out? Two noises there and David Warner has taken a great diving catch. The two umpires get together and want to check if that catch is taken cleanly or not. It is. Australia have a big breakthrough.
Lovely delivery! Draws Dimuth Karunaratne into the drive. This is tossed up on off. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge to cover-point.
Goes slightly fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it away to mid-wicket for an easy single.
On a length, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne defends it towards the off side.
Well played! Cummins with a half-volley, outside off. Angelo Mathews takes a good stride forward and drives it through covers. The fielder runs behind it and cuts it off as the batters run three.
Delivers it full on off at 131 kph. Angelo Mathews drives it crisply but straight to mid on.
Goes a tad shorter on off. Angelo Mathews rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Lands on a length, on off. Angelo Mathews defends it solidly onto the turf.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end. 6-3-12-1 are his figures so far.
Beaten! Short and wide outside off. Turn and bounce there as Dimuth Karunaratne misses his cut shot.
This is fuller on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne takes a good stride forward and blocks it.
Goes quicker again, on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne gets his bat down in time.
Flatter one on off. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it out.
Pitches it around off and it turns away. Dimuth Karunaratne lets the ball come and guides it to the left of the second slip fielder.
Regarding 26.5 - The UltraEdge is shown now and there indeed was the involvement of the gloves. Eagle eye, Marnus!
Angles it on the pads from 'round the wicket. Dimuth Karunaratne clips it to deep square leg for a couple.

Welcome back to the afternoon session! The Australian players are out there in the middle. Dimuth Karunaratne and Angelo Mathews also walk out to resume their innings. It will be Nathan Lyon to start with the ball. Here we go...
… DAY 1, SESSION 2 …

Australia will be quietly pleased with the way this match has gone so far. All their bowlers have looked in control and stuck to good lines. They will be hoping for more of the same in the afternoon session and dislodging the current partnership quickly will be on top of their agenda as it involves two of Sri Lanka's most experienced players. Do join us at 12.40 pm IST (7.10 am GMT) for the post-Lunch session.

A fine two hours of Test cricket comes to a close. Sri Lanka won a crucial toss on this surface, and it was a no-brainer to bat first. However, losing two wickets, that too off needless attempts, would be hurting them. Pat Cummins and Mitchell Starc bowled disciplined lines and were quite effective. Nathan Lyon was introduced into the attack in the sixth over, and his first ball was enough to indicate what was to come. Plenty of spin and bounce on offer, and batting certainly is very tough, but credit to the Lankan batters for not losing a single wicket to spin in the morning session. Had Australia reviewed that decision against Dimuth Karunaratne in the last over, things could have been different though.
Dot to end the session! Nice loopy delivery on off. Angelo Mathews gets well forward and defends it out comfortably. That will be Lunch on Day 1! Sri Lanka are 68/2!

Big appeal but not given! This is on middle and leg. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to sweep but misses. He is rapped up on the pads and there is an appeal but the umpire says no. Australia do not take the review as Marnus Labuschagne, who is always enthusiastic regarding the DRS, tells his skipper that it came off the gloves. Hang on, the replays later show that it might have missed the gloves. It was pitching on leg and hitting the leg stump. A chance missed, perhaps.
Tossed up, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it out.
Tossed up on off. Dimuth Karunaratne drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne drives but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball goes to the left of the bowler.
Shorter and flatter on off. Angelo Mathews backs away and cuts it to deep point for a single.
Shorter and outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne punches it towards the off side.
Shorter length on middle. Angelo Mathews works it to deep square leg for a single.
Nice loopy delivery that turns in from off. Angelo Mathews reaches the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Slower through the air on middle. Angelo Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle from 'round the wicket. Angelo Mathews nudges it towards the leg side.
Shorter length on middle, Angelo Mathews works it straight to short fine leg.
A flatter one on middle, Angelo Mathews goes back and works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Shorter length on leg. Dimuth Karunaratne pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Turn this time, pitches it on off and it turns in. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to defend but gets hit high on his pads.
Beaten! Swepson pushes it quicker outside off. It does not turn and Dimuth Karunaratne is beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend.
Tossed up on off. Angelo Mathews drives it to long off for a single.
Swepson with a quicker delivery on off. Angelo Mathews defends it off the front foot.
A flatter one on off. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it out.
Pulls his length back a bit and it turns away as well. It is outside off and Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it.
FOUR! Dimuth Karunaratne plays it against the spin but plays it well! Tossed up on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne gets low and slog-sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Slower through the air this time on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne with a solid block.
Goes quicker and flatter on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up, outside off. Angelo Mathews skips down the track and works it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is full but on the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne sweeps and sweeps it well. The ball runs towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Flatter and on off, punched back down the ground and Swepson stopped it with a slide to his left.
Lovely variation to beat the outside edge. This one is pushed quicker through the air, landing around off and skids away, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to defend from the back foot but misses.
Beauty! Floated leg spinner, landing a bit short and around off, Dimuth Karunaratne goes back to cut but is cramped for room. It clips his gloves and falls down on the surface.
A flatter delivery on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne works it towards the leg side.
Mitchell Swepson starts with a wayward delivery down the leg side. Angelo Mathews leaves it. Carey fails to collect it cleanly as well and a bye is taken as the ball rolls behind the keeper.
Mitchell Swepson to have a go now.
Shorter and outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne waits for it and guides it towards the gully region.
Turning away from around off, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to sweep but misses.

Ohh...tough chance goes down! This is fuller on off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets on the front foot and pushes it with the full face of his bat. It goes straight to silly point. Marnus Labuschagne there is late to react and the ball hits his body.
Presses forward and defends it towards silly point.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted and full, around leg, swept behind square leg for a single.

Bit of excitement there but nothing more than that! Back of a length, angling into leg. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits Dimuth Karunaratne high on his pads and rolls towards the off side.
Nicely bowled! A yorker on off, Dimuth Karunaratne is also equal to the task and blocks it out.
Back of a length on middle at 142 kph. Angelo Mathews works it away to fine leg for a single.
Lands on a length, around off at 140 kph. Angelo Mathews defends it off the outside half of his blade to point.
Bangs it short, around off at 143 kph. Angelo Mathews pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Starc with a length delivery on off at 141 kph. Angelo Mathews defends it solidly off the front foot.
Quicker and shorter outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne stays back to play at it late but it goes straight to second slip, on the bounce.
Skidding down the leg side, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to work it on the leg side but it takes the leading half and rolls back in the direction of the bowler.
Lunges to a full ball and defends it solidly.
Slower through the air, full and around middle and leg, Dimuth tries to sweep but misses. He is hit on the pads, the close-in fielders appeal but nothing doing.
Quicker and fuller, around off and skidding in, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Flatter and around off, Dimuth Karunaratne punches it from the back foot to covers.
FOUR! That's a very good shot! Starc pitches it up and around off, Angelo Mathews gets forward and just shows the full face of his bat as he eases it down the ground through mid off.
Fraction short and on off, at 139 kph, Mathews goes on his toes and defends it down on the pitch.
Fuller and around off, angling away, Mathews pushes it to covers.
Fuller in length and around off, Mathews gets a bit forward and defends it again towards mid off.
Lands it on a good length, around middle and off, Mathews gets behind the line and blocks it down.
Back of a length, around off at 142 clicks, Mathews sits on the back foot and defends it towards mid off.
Flighted and full, outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne strides forward and drives it to point.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it down watchfully.
Beaten! Perfect line and length around off. Drifting in around off and turning away, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to defend from the back foot but is beaten by the extra bounce and spin.
Spinning down the leg side, Mathews nudges it through square leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, driven through the line but straight to wide mid off.
Floated delivery, full and around off, Mathews dances down the track and defends it with his bat and pad together.
Fuller and close to off, defended solidly by Karunaratne to end the over. A successful one for Australia.
Serves it on a length, around off and shaping in a bit, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to defend but it takes the inner half and rolls to square leg.
On a length but around leg, Mathews tucks it in the gap at mid-wicket and gets off the mark with a single.
Full again, close to off, Mathews shows a dead bat as he jams it down safely.
Well bowled and well played too. Fuller in length, around off, Angelo Mathews gets across his stumps a bit and defends it down.
Angelo Mathews is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mitchell Starc returns and strikes with the first ball of a new spell. He speeds in from over the wicket and delivers it on a fuller length outside off at 139 kph. This one goes on with the angle of the bowler as Kusal Mendis tries to be adventurous, attempting to drive without any footwork. A thick outside edge is generated and Alex Carey has an easy catch to take. A very poor shot selection from Mendis and both the batters dismissed so far have gifted their wickets away.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: Mitchell Starc is back into the attack. Four overs for 16 runs so far!
Another half-tracker outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne camps back and forces it through the line, but again finds point.
Flatter and shorter, outside off, DM cuts but finds the point fielder.
Loopy and full, around off, Dimuth Karunaratne lunges and defends it from the outer half of his bat.
Flighted and around off, defended off the back foot.
Tossed up, around off, punched from the back foot to point.

Beauty! Lyon goes wide of the crease and slows it down. Delivers it full and around off. It turns a shade with some extra bounce and strikes Karunaratne on the gloves as he presses to defend. The ball falls in front of silly point.
Too full this time, getting the batter to drive, Mendis strokes it off the front foot but finds the cover fielder.
Fuller in length and on off, at 134 kph, Mendis stays put and defends it to point.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Mendis presents a defensive angled bat and it travels to the right of the gully fielder.
Cummins keeps it full and around off, this time Mendis drives it towards the cover fielder.
Pitches it up and around off, Kusal drives it from the middle of his bat but straight towards the bowler. Pat makes the stop in his followthrough.
Serves it on a good length and outside off, Kusal Mendis shoulders arms.
Slider, around off and skidding in, Dimuth Karunaratne sticks on the back foot and keeps it out at the last moment. Superb bowling from Lyon.
Extra bounce this time, outside off as it turns away, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes at it nervously from the back foot and it goes off the outer edge to point.
Floated delivery, full and outside off, Mendis drives it through covers, against the turn but places it well. The batters run three.

SHOUT FOR A BAT-PAD! The finger has stayed down and Pat Cummins gets convinced to take the DRS. Flighted delivery, full and around middle, Kusal Mendis leans forward and tries to flick but doesn't close the face of his bat entirely. It loops off the pads to short leg where the fielder dives to catch it with one hand. The UltraEdge detects no bat. Then, the third umpire also checks the Ball Tracking for lbw but it shows that the ball is missing the stumps by a long way. Australia lose a review.
Tossed up, around off and turning in a bit, Mendis goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Loopy delivery, outside off, Karunaratne guides it wide of second slip and to the right of backward point. He takes a single.
Full in length and around off, Kusal defends it solidly from the crease. A wicket maiden for Cummins.

That missed the off pole by a whisker and Pat Cummins is on his haunches in disbelief. The speedster delivers it from wide of the crease and lands it just outside off. It pitches and moves back in a bit as the batter decides to not offer any shot.
A tempter outside off, there to be driven, Kusal Mendis leaves it in the end. Has a big smile on his face, he resisted the temptation there.
Full again, around off at 136 kph, Mendis defends it by opening the face of his body. It rolls to covers.
Fuller in length, around off, Kusal Mendis defends it by covering the line.

DRINKS! Both the Sri Lankan openers looked solid for the most part of the last hour but Pat Cummins has done well to get a much-needed breakthrough for the Aussies here! The pitch has shown signs of turn and bounce in the first hour itself and it looks like a tough task for the batters and they need to apply themselves here. Kusal Mendis joins his skipper now and both batters would be looking to take their team to Lunch without further damage.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! This wicket is against the run of play. Pat Cummins has produced the goods. He serves it on a good length outside off at 133 kph and gets it to bounce a bit extra. Pathum Nissanka sits on the back foot, could have left it alone but decides to flirt inside the line of the delivery. He ends up getting a thick outside edge and Alex Carey catches the ball by stretching across to his right. Australia are delighted!
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, full and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne presses forward and push-drives it to short cover.
Uses the spin and this time sends it to deep square leg for a single.
Spinning in from around off, Pathum Nissanka works it wide of leg slip.
Flatter and shorter around off, defended off the back foot.

Floated and around off, turning back in, Pathum Nissanka advances down the track and tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to leg slip where David Warner catches the ball. Small appeal dies down immediately.
Turn and bounce from a full length around off, Pathum Nissanka leans to defend but misses and is hit high on the back foot.
Delivers it on a length around off, Pathum Nissanka taps it down to covers and steals a run. This has been a feature of this partnership so far.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Pathum Nissanka stands squared up inside the crease as he defends it down safely.
Fraction short in length and outside off, Dimuth goes on his back foot and pushes it in the gap at extra cover for a single. All too easy for Sri Lanka at the moment.
Back of a length, around off, some extra lift there for the bowler, Dimuth Karunaratne goes on his toes and defends it down on the leg side.
On a good length, around middle and leg, Pathum Nissanka works it behind square leg and picks up a single.

FOUR! Pathum Nissanka loves playing square of the wicket, on both sides. Pat Cummins digs it in short, around off, the bounce though is not threatening and Pathum Nissanka stands back to pull it with ease. The key is the placement which is in front of square leg and it races away to the fence.
Lyon pulls his length back. Dimuth Karunaratne stays back and lets it turn and then defends it towards the off side.
Gives it some more air on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it off the front foot.
Goes fuller on off, Dimuth Karunaratne drives it to short extra cover.
Short again from Lyon. Nissanka pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Tad shorter, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it to cover-point and takes a single.
Tossed up on middle at 89 kph. Dimuth Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Serves a good-length delivery on off, Nissanka defends it solidly off the front foot.
Goes fuller on middle, at 138 kph. Nissanka works it to mid on.
Back of a length, on middle, Nissanka blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Top shot from a top player! Cummins with a bouncer, on off. Nissanka picks the length quickly and gets on top of the bounce to pull it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Pulls his length back, on off. Nissanka defends it towards the off side.
Goes fuller on off. Nissanka blocks it off the front foot.
Pat Cummins comes back into the attack, this time from the opposite end, replacing Mitchell Starc.
Nicely flighted delivery on off. A hint of turn but Dimuth Karunaratne covers it and defends off the front foot.
Shorter and outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it to the point fielder.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it off the front foot.
This is fuller, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to drive but gets the inside edge of his blade. It goes past the stumps and wide of the keeper, and the batters run two.
Around middle, swept to deep square leg for a run.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Nissanka reaches the pitch of the ball and blocks it out.
Back of a length, on middle. Nissanka works it behind square leg for a single.
Starc tries a short delivery, on off. Nissanka pulls it through square leg for a couple.
On a length, on off, Nissanka blocks it off the front foot.

Ohh.. that has taken off! Starc with a length delivery, around off. Nissanka looks to drive but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it is angled across and bounces sharply. Carey collects it over his head.
Keeps it full on middle. Nissanka defends it off the front foot.
Wow! Starc with a very full delivery on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne works it towards fine leg for a single.
Lyon keeps his length short, it pitches outside off and turns into Nissanka. He blocks it off the back foot, in front of the keeper.
Goes fuller on off. Dimuth Karunaratne drives it towards the off side and takes a single right under short cover's nose.
This time he pulls his length back, it is outside off and turns away. Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it to towards point.
Drifts on the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to deep square leg for a couple.
A quicker one on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it this time.

Concussion test, for Alex Carey. Extra bounce on the last delivery and he gets hit bang on the helmet while trying to gather the ball. The Australian physio rushes out and it's a quick test. Ready to resume...

Goodness me, first ball from a spinner in this Test match and it has turned and bounced. Ominous signs. Lyon starts off with a peach of a delivery! He comes 'round the wicket. Tosses this up on middle and leg. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to work it towards the leg side. However, the ball turns sharply to beat Dimuth Karunaratne. It bounces sharply as well and hits Alex Carey on his helmet!
As expected, Nathan Lyon has been introduced into the attack.
Lands on a good length and it is angled across the batter at 139 kph. Nissanka leaves it alone.
Good running! Back of a length, on leg. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to work it away but misses. The ball hits his thigh and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Lands on a length, on off. Nissanka pushes it gently towards covers and takes a single.
Drifting on the pads this time. Dimuth Karunaratne clips it to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Confident shot from the Lankan captain! Starc pitches it up again, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne leans forward and drives it through covers for a lovely boundary. Balance was the key there for Dimuth Karunaratne!
Starc looks for some swing and bowls it full but down the leg side. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to flick it but misses.
The ball has not moved much to bother the batters here. We might see Pat Cummins employing a spinner with this hard new ball soon.
On a length, on middle, at 139 kph. Nissanka defends it off the middle of his blade to mid on.
Goes a tad fuller on off, Nissanka pushes but gets the inside half of his blade as the ball rolls to mid on.
Continues to land it on a good length, on off, Nissanka blocks it out.
On a length and close to off this time. Nissanka connects with his defense.
Absolute beauty! Lands on a good length, outside off. Pathum Nissanka looks to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball shapes away a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Cummins comes 'round the wicket and goes fuller on off. Dimuth Karunaratne drives it off the inside half of his blade towards mid-wicket for a single. He is off the mark!
Starc with almost a yorker, outside off at 138 kph. Nissanka digs it out. Both the Lankan batters are looking solid so far!
This is pitched up but outside off again and Nissanka lets it go.
Pulls his length back and it is outside off. Nissanka leaves it alone.
FOUR! Good shot! First boundary of the game! Overpitched on off. Nissanka shows the full face of his blade and drives it straight down the ground for a boundary at long on.

That's a dangerous delivery! After bowling deliveries that come into the right-hander, he angled this across the batter. Lands on a length and around off. Nissanka looks to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge of his blade.
A fullish delivery, around off. Nissanka defends it towards the off side off his front foot.
Lands on a length, on off. The Sri Lankan captain makes a solid block off the front foot. Maiden from Pat Cummins to start!
Back of a length, on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it to mid-wicket.
Beautiful delivery! Lands on a good length, around off. It seams back in sharply this time and beats Dimuth Karunaratne completely as he looks to defend it. Beats the inside edge of his blade there!
Goes fuller this time, on off. Dimuth Karunaratne is solid in defense again. This is a good start from Australia, they are making the batters play almost every ball here.
Bowls it on the off pole line. On a length again and Dimuth Karunaratne defends it towards the off side.
Lands on a length, around off. Some movement away from the left-hander and Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Pulls his length back slightly, around off. Nissanka blocks it off the front foot. Good start from Starc, on the money straight away!
Pat Cummins to speed in from the other end.
Starc goes fuller and outside off. Pathum Nissanka looks to drive but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball rolls towards the leg side.
Starc is fuller again, on off. Nissanka with a solid block off the front foot.
Ohh...late swing for Starc! He targets the stumps this time. Very full and shaping into the batter. Nissanka gets his bat down in time and gets a couple of runs as the ball travels past mid off.
Goes full again, on off at 140 kph. Nissanka drives firmly and the fielder at short cover stops it with a slide.
Starc starts with a fullish delivery, around off. Good shape into the batter for Starc. Pathum Nissanka though makes a good leave.

Right then, we're done with all the pre-match formalities and it's time for the real action to begin. The Australian players are spreading on the field and Mitchell Starc is marking his run-up. Out come the Sri Lankan openers, Dimuth Karunaratne and Pathum Nissanka. The Lankan captain had a tough time against Starc on the last tour of Australia here as he was dismissed five times by the speedster. All in readiness, here we go...

The players from both sides have lined up in the middle. It's time for the national anthems of both sides. Australia's first and then Sri Lanka's. We're done with the anthems and now the players are observing a minute's silence in the memory of our beloved Shane Keith Warne.

Pitch report - The surface looks fine and it's a typical Galle pitch. It's hard in nature but some of the cracks are moving already. Putting runs on the board will be the way forward. Spinners will dominate and the batters will have to work hard for their runs.
Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey (WK), Pat Cummins (C), Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Mitchell Swepson.

Sri Lanka (Playing XI) - Pathum Nissanka, Dimuth Karunaratne (C), Kusal Mendis, Angelo Mathews, Dhananjaya de Silva, Dinesh Chandimal, Niroshan Dickwella (WK), Ramesh Mendis, Jeffrey Vandersay (On Test debut), Lasith Embuldeniya, Asitha Fernando.

Pat Cummins, the Aussie skipper, says he would have batted first as well but now hopes that there will be some swing early on. Smiles and adds that they have managed to put up a XI and informs that Travis Head has passed the fitness test and is playing. Further shares that their team combination is about two seamers, two spinners and a couple of all-rounders. Tells that it's a bit unfortunate to have Josh Hazlewood on the bench as they are going in with Mitchell Starc.

Dimuth Karunaratne, the captain of Sri Lanka, says that they know how the ball will behave on the last two days and hence this decision. He confirms the Test debut of Jeffrey Vandersay and informs that they are going with three genuine spinners and one seamer.
Toss - Up goes the coin, Pat Cummins calls it wrongly and SRI LANKA ELECT TO BAT!

Weather update - The forecast is expected to be good for the day but there were some early morning showers. As a precaution, we can see the covers out there, however, the main playing area is uncovered. Fingers crossed.
We are all set to start. Australian players have made their way out in the middle. Dimuth Karunaratne and Pathum Nissanka will start the innngs. Mitchell Starc comes to bowl.
...THIRD INNINGS...

Sri Lanka would be a tad disappointed with their bowling effort on Day 2, as they could've ended way early, but could not be disciplined throughout. Nonetheless, they would be happy to end things quite early on the moving day. The hosts will be back in no time with the blade to chase down the trail and put up a target for the Aussies. Stay tuned.

Australia walk out with a lead of 109 runs. After putting on a brisk 35 at end of Day 2, Lyon and Cummins were unable to expand their stand as much as they would've liked to. Australia have their noses in front here and would be hoping to display excellent spells with the ball just like the previous innings. Alex Carey and Cameron Green were the ones who put Australia in the driving seat.

OUT! BOWLED! Australia are bundled out! Sri Lanka have done well as they have not allowed the tail to wag much! Asitha Fernando again gets a good amount of inward swing, this is full and around middle. Mitchell Swepson is too late to get his bat down and the ball disturbs the stumps behind. Australia lead by 109 runs.
Commentary.Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary.Commentary: Full toss on the pads, flicked to fine leg for a single.

A mix up but Swepson makes his ground! A fuller ball, slanting around middle and leg. Swepson fails to flick it away and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to covers and there is a yes or no for a quick single. Swepson is rushing to the bowler's end and he makes his ground as Fernando misses his shy.
Who will walk out now?

OUT! TIMBER! A beauty of a delivery from Asitha Fernando! Pat Cummins was rather expecting a short ball but this is a yorker, around off and swinging in. Pat Cummins hangs back as he looks to block it out but misses and the ball shatters the stumps. Good start by Sri Lanka.
Commentary.Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller ball, tailing on the pads. Lyon whips it to deep square leg for a single.
Asitha Fernando comes into the attack.
Flatter ball, around middle and leg. Cummins stays back and blocks it out.
A single now! Fuller ball on middle. Lyon sweeps it hard and through square leg for a single.
Tossed up, slower through the air, on middle. Lyon sweeps it to square leg. No run there.
Slightly short and outside off. Lyon looks to reverse-sweep it but misses.
FOUR! Lyon and Australia are off the mark on Day 3! Full again, around off. Lyon this time reverse-sweeps it and hits it fine to third man for a boundary. Good shot that!
Tosses it up, full and angling across, outside off. Lyon tries to sweep it but misses.
We are all set for the action of Day 3. The players are out in the middle. Nathan Lyon and Pat Cummins will resume their innings. Ramesh Mendis to start the proceedings with the ball.

Breaking News - Angelo Mathews has tested positive for Covid. He will not take any further part in this match. Oshada Fernando is his replacement in this match.Pitch Report with Russel Arnold: There are lots of crumbling around, Ramesh and Lyon were effective from either side and there are places the bowlers can target. The batters stride out and find themselves in trouble. The real key is to go at the ball. If the batter is in the crease he will be in trouble.

Nathan Lyon is up for a chat. He says Green and Carey are young in Test cricket but he is very proud of them for the way they have performed. . Adds that as a bowler he wants to be on the mark and put the best ball out there. He says that the plan was always to put the pressure on the bat and to bowl well. Chuckles and says he enjoys batting.

Sri Lanka are playing with four spinners but are not optimizing the pitch to the best. That was a big difference in two days - how Lyon and Swepson operated and were so productive as compared to the Lankan spinners. Ramesh Mendis was the best of the lot and they will hope to take the remaining two wickets immediately. The forecast looks much better than we had on Day 2 and we hope there are no interruptions this time. Stay tuned for any other updates

The pitch is not the easiest to bat on but this mighty Aussie team have shown their batting skills on a difficult pitch and currently be ahead in the match. It was Usman Khawaja first and then Cameron Green played a brilliant innings along with Alex Carey to take the lead. There is not much batting left now but Cummins can try and hit a few lusty blows and add as many runs to the lead as possible.

Hello everyone! Welcome to the action of Day 3 of this first Test match between Sri Lanka and Australia. The game is slightly in the visitors' favor as they lead by 101 runs and with 2 wickets still in hand. The Aussies will be happy if Pat Cummins and Nathan Lyon can grind more runs and breach the 150-lead. Sri Lanka on the other hand will hope to bundle them out quickly by taking the remaining wickets quickly.
... Day 3, Session 1...

Australia have put themselves in the driver's seat. A lead of over 100 will be already bothering the home team and the visitors are not done yet. Pat Cummins and Nathan Lyon will be looking to swell it further to push Sri Lanka further on the back foot. Friday is going to bring more engrossing Test cricket our way. It will be an early start. The first ball on Day 3 will be at 9.45 am IST (4.15 am GMT) but you can join us in advance for the build-up. Cheers!

It's a brave batting effort by the Australian team, especially from their lower-order batters. The day started with them trailing by over 100 runs and they lost Travis Head pretty quickly as well but then Cameron Green arrived at the crease with positive intent. He threaded three vital stands with Usman Khawaja, Alex Carey and Mitchell Starc, and played a crucial role in helping Australia gain a handy lead. A special mention for Alex Carey who played his reverse sweeps with great aplomb and reminded us of Andy Flower. His quickfire knock propelled Australia as he put the Lankan bowlers to the sword.

End of Day 2 and it belonged to only two parties - Rain in the first session and Australia in the following two sessions. Sri Lanka were absent. In spin-friendly conditions, where the likes of Muttiah Muralitharan and Rangana Herath used to dominate the touring batters, the current crop of spinners failed to leave a mark. Bowling with consistent accuracy - an art that all the three genuine spinners lacked. To an extent, Ramesh Mendis did manage to gain some control, but overall, it was a dismal show from the Lankan spinners, especially in the afternoon session.

It's officially Stumps on Day 2. This was inevitable once they left the park so late in the evening. Right then, a lead of 101 for Australia and they will be immensely pleased with the outcome of this rain-hit day.
Bad light! The umpires have decided that the play cannot continue any further for now. The players are off the field. It's not Stumps yet but it's tough to see the light improving from here on.
SIX! Gigantic! Floated one, full and around off, Pat Cummins goes down on one knee and launches it over wide long on for a maximum. 16 from the over. Lead crosses 100!
Shorter, a googly, around middle. Pat Cummins blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Pat Cummins continues to attack Jeffrey Vandersay! Another full ball, around middle and off. Pat Cummins sweeps this towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Spinning away from the batter, outside off, Pat leaves it alone.
Fullish and around off, Cummins pushes it to covers from the middle of his bat. Niroshan Dickwella appeals thinking that it came off the pads. Funny!
SIX! The Aussie skipper is on the attack. Flatter and fuller, around middle, Cummins clears his front leg and hammers it over mid-wicket.

A huge shout for an LBW, but the umpire disagrees! A loopy ball, full, around middle. Nathan Lyon gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pads. That was probably spinning down leg.
A bit short and around leg, Cummins flicks it of his back foot to mid-wicket for a single.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, turning in, Lyon goes down for the sweep but the ball hits his pads and goes towards fine leg. They get a single.
On a length outside off, Cummins leans and drives it to long off. They take a single.
Tossed up on middle, Lyon goes down and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a run.
Fuller delivery on off, Lyon sweeps it but it hits his foot and the ball stays on the pitch. It looks like he is hurt a bit.
The light meter is out! The umpires have checked the light and it seems fine for now! We are good to resume.
Googly this time from Jeffrey Vandersay from outside off, Pat Cummins gets well behind the line of the ball and defends.
Full once again outside off. Pat Cummins tries to play for the turn but the ball keeps its line and beats the outside edge.

SIX! Pat Cummins gets a hold of this one! Jeffrey Vandersay feeds the batter with a flighted delivery, full and on middle. Pat Cummins thumps this straight and really high up right behind the bowler for a biggie! Useful runs here for Australia.
Nathan Lyon gets a stride forward and plays the full delivery outside off towards cover for a single.
Attempts the sweep but misses, Full and turning in from wide outside off and strikes the batsman on his legs. Brief appeal but the ball is clearly hitting outside the line of the stumps.
Flighted full on off, Pat Cummins goes for a big shot but only manages an inside edge towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Fuller one down the leg side, Nathan Lyon gets on his knees and sweeps it past backward square leg for a boundary.
Shorter one on middle, Pat Cummins flicks it towards fine leg for one.
On a length and on the middle, Lyon slogsweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
A bit short on the middle, turning in. Lyon tries to play at it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Shout for LBW but the finger remains down.
A bit full outside off, Lyon tries to play it on the off side but it hits the inside edge of his bat and goes to short leg.
Quicker length delivery on middle, Lyon manages to defend it back to the bowler.
Tosses this one up, full, and around the leg pole. Pat Cummins leans and blocks it out watchfully.
Shorter one, around middle. Pat Cummins stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Nathan Lyon is off the mark with a sweep shot. Jeffrey Vandersay bowls this full on off, Nathan Lyon connects this time and gets a single to backward square leg.
Slightly shorter and outside off. Nathan Lyon attempts to sweep this time but misses.
Nathan Lyon walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Jeffrey Vandersay comes into the attack and strikes right away! Full delivery outside off, Mitchell Starc aims for a heave across the line but ends up dragging it off the inner half, straight to the left of the bowler, who dives and takes a lovely catch with both his hands. Flings the ball in the air in celebration and Sri Lanka are looking to run through the tail.
Commentary.Howout: c & b Jeffrey Vandersay

Commentary.Commentary: Jeffrey Vandersay starts off with a full delivery spinning in from outside off, Mitchell Starc tries to slog but misses the line of the ball.
Jeffrey Vandersay comes to bowl!
Full and on the middle, Cummins blocks it off his back foot. A successful over for the Sri Lankans.

OUT! LBW! Ramesh Mendis gets rid of a well-set batter here! He grabs his fourth wicket of the game and Australia have lost their seventh. A much-needed wicket for Sri Lanka! Cameron Green departs after an exceptional knock. A loopy ball, this one lands around off and spins in sharply. Cameron Green gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pads. A huge shout for LBW, and the umpire raises his finger! Cameron Green opts for a review! No bat is involved, confirms the UltraEdge, and the Ball Tracking shows three reds. Cameron Green has to walk back. Pat Cummins is the new man in!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary.Commentary: Quicker and full outside off, Green uses his feet but finds the bowler again.
Slower through the air on off, Starc pushes it to deep backward point for a run.
A bit short and on leg, Green pulls it of his back foot towards deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on the middle, Green steps out and defends it back towards the bowler.
Full once again outside leg stump, Cameron Green gets back and knocks it towards long on for a single.
Lasith Embuldeniya continues bowling outside leg and full. Cameron Green puts his pad to this one.
Really wide down the leg side and full, Cameron Green tries to sweep but misses.
Slightly short and spinning in from outside off, Mitchell Starc goes back into the crease and punches it through covers for one run.
Flighted full outside leg, Cameron Green gets to the pitch of the delivery and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Lasith Embuldeniya goes over the wicket to the right-hander. Pitches it a fraction short outside leg, Cameron Green punches it back to the bowler.

DRINKS! Australia might have lost the wicket of Alex Carey, but they are still manoeuvring along nicely. Their lead is now 61 and they will be aiming to get a lead of 100 by the end of the day. Cameron Green is looking good in the middle and he is heading towards his ton accompanied by Starc who has scored 8 runs off 26 deliveries. Sri Lanka have all allowed Australia to build another partnership here. They need to grab quick wickets to stay in this game!

FOUR BYES! Brilliant delivery but no reward for the bowler. It's nicely tossed up, landing full and around off, Mitchell Starc tries to play straight but gets beaten. It misses the off stump by a whisker and stays low as well to go through the legs of the keeper.
Presses forward to a full ball and pushes it to covers.
Beaten again. Spinning away from the batter, Starc tries to defend but misses again due to the away spin.
Quicker and shorter on off, Starc goes on the back foot and punches it to covers.
Beautiful! Lovely drift into the batter, landing on a fuller length around off and turning square, Starc is forward in defense but gets beaten.
Drifting in around off, fuller in length, Green comes down the track and forces it to long off for a single.
Fuller and outside off, spinning in sharply, Starc presses forward to drive but it takes the inner edge and goes to short mid-wicket.
Excellent shot! Full and wide outside off, Green goes down and sweeps it all along the ground to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter through the air, around off and turning in, Starc goes on the back foot and hits it past short mid-wicket for a single.
Allows the ball to spin back in from around off and helps it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, fuller in length, it's defended back to the bowler.
Spinning down the leg side, it's pushed quicker through the air, Starc leaves it alone.
Advances down the track and defends a full ball back to the bowler. Ramesh Mendis has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.

FOUR! The Australians are finding ways to score runs. Loopy delivery, full and spinning down the leg side, Green attempts to play the conventional sweep but it takes the back of his bat and runs down to third man for a boundary.
Flighted and around off, spinning in, Green walks down the track and defends it off the inner edge to silly mid on.
Much fuller this time, around leg, Starc digs it out from the outer half of his blade. The ball rolls to short third man and they cross. AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 50 RUNS!
Short and wide outside off, Starc goes back and flashes his bat at it. Connects only with thin air.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Starc defends it off his front foot.
Full and flighted, around off, Green walks forward and drives it towards short cover. The fielder there makes a partial stop.
Fullish and on off, Green runs down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Fires it full and around leg, Starc sweeps and it deflects off short leg to mid-wicket. They cross.
Fuller and on off, Starc tries to defend and does so off the inner half to short mid-wicket.
IN THE AIR... Falls safely. Loopy and full, around leg, Green again tries to sweep but it takes the top half of his bat. The ball flies to deep square leg and drops safely. They take one.
FOUR! Embuldeniya continues to leak boundaries. Too full in length and drifting down the leg side, Green goes down and sweeps it delightfully to the deep backward square leg fence.
Lasith Embuldeniya comes to bowl now.
Quite wide outside off to bother the batter, Starc offers no shot.
This one skids into the batter with the angle, on middle, Green bunts it to mid on and picks up a single.
Beaten! A little bit of late away movement there, perhaps some reverse movement, on a length and outside off, Green pushes inside the line and misses.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Green tries to help it away off his pads but misses.
Short and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Delivers it on a length and around leg, Green clips it to square leg and rotates the strike.
Leans forward to a full ball around off and pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Slower through the air but it lands in the blackhole, Starc digs it out as a spray of dust comes off the pitch.
FOUR! Poor delivery. Short in length and wide outside off, Mitchell Starc immediately goes on the back foot and whacks it through cover-point. Opens his account.
Fuller and on off, defended back.
Edged but safe! Loopy delivery, full and around off, Starc tries to defend off the front foot but it spins away to take the outside edge. It doesn't carry to first slip.
Fuller and around off, Green drives it down to long off for a single.
Shortish and around leg, Starc tries to work it around but misses. It goes behind the wickets off his body.

Another slight halt! Mitchell Starc has been struck on his helmet while trying to duck to a short ball. The physio is out there conducting the mandatory concussion test. Also, Mitchell Starc needs a new helmet!
Bang on the helmet! A sharp bouncer, around middle and skidding into the batter, Starc takes his eyes off the ball as he tries to get away. He fails and is hit on the helmet.
Mitchell Starc seems to have cracked the bottom part of his bat. He has asked for a replacement.
Asitha Fernando eyes the blockhole, Starc does well to dig it out towards mid on. Has he broken his bat? Yes.
Back of a length, around leg, Green helps it from the back foot to square leg and collects a single.
Slower bouncer around leg with a leg gully in place, Cameron Green reads the plan and ducks.
Skiddy delivery, full and down the leg side, Green attempts to flick off his pads but misses. Niroshan Dickwella dives across to his left and collects the ball.
Play and a miss. Floated delivery, landing full around middle and spinning away, Starc draws forward to defend but it whistles past the outside edge.
Uses his feet again and this time plays a full ball from the inner half of his bat. The ball runs down to long on and they cross.
FOUR! That's a good shot! Too full in length and outside off, Cameron Green uses his feet to reach the pitch of the ball and drills it through covers.
Mitchell Starc is the new man in

OUT! CAUGHT! That's a fine running catch by Dinesh Chandimal. The 84-run stand has been broken and Sri Lanka can take a huge sigh of relief. Ramesh Mendis hurls it across on a fuller length, around off and turning away, Alex Carey attempts for a big heave across the line but due to the away spin, the ball catches the toe end of his bat and flies behind mid off. Dinesh Chandimal scoots behind, keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a very good catch as he goes down. Australia lead by 29 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Dinesh Chandimal b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary.Commentary: Another fuller ball, around middle and leg. Cameron Green sweeps once again this time towards deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Cameron Green brings up his fifty in style! It's been a classy knock so far. Fuller one, around off. Cameron Green gets down on his knee and sweeps it powerfully through mid-wicket for a boundary. He will want to convert this into a big one!
Good-length delivery, angling this one in, around middle and leg. Alex Carey flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, darting on the pads. Cameron Green hangs back and tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Shorter one, around middle and off. Cameron Green ducks and lets that go through to the keeper.
Asitha Fernando hits the deck hard again, serves it short, around middle and leg. Cameron Green ducks underneath it.
A loud appeal for caught behind, but the umpire says no! Asitha Fernando drops it short now, around the leg pole. Cameron Green tries to pull this but he fails to get any bat on it.
Pitches this one up, around middle and leg, angling in. Alex Carey tries to flick this one but he manages to get a slight inside edge back onto his pads and towards fine eg. A single taken!
Who will bowl from the other end? Asitha Fernando it is!
Swing and a miss! Fuller, around middle and leg. Cameron Green gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this one but he misses.
Tosses it up, full, around off. Cameron Green advances down the track and tries to defend but he misses. The ball hits his pads and lobs up towards short leg.
Pitches it up, on middle. Cameron Green defends it out.
Outside off, a tad shorter. Cameron Green cuts it towards point.
Full from over the wicket now, around middle. Cameron Green defends this one but the ball goes off the inside edge and falls short of forward short leg.
Australia and Alex Carey are up and running in the final session! Fuller one, around middle. Alex Carey reverse-sweeps it towards point for a single.

We are back for the final session on Day 2! 32 overs are still left to be bowled in this final session, let's hope we get to witness all of them. The players have made their way out to the middle. Alex Carey and Cameron Green will resume their batting for Australia. Ramesh Mendis will begin with the proceedings with the ball. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

The pitch is doing all sorts of things for the spinners, there is bounce and turn on offer. But the batters have found a way to tackle them. Jeffrey Vandersay and Dhananjaya de Silva were the wicket-takers, while Lasith Embuldeniya continues to struggle. Sri Lanka will need to pick wickets in a heap in the next session and not let Australia get away with a big lead. Do join us at 4.05 pm IST (10.35 am GMT) to see how the final session of the day pans out.

After a big delay, Sri Lanka began the proceedings perfectly on Day 2 as they got rid of Travis Head in the second over of the day.
