Post that, the overnight batter, Usman Khawaja and Cameron Green tackled the spin well. The duo stitched together 57 runs before Khawaja fell prey to Jeffrey Vandersay. He was dismissed for a well-made 71. The momentum had swung towards Sri Lanka but they failed to capitalize on that. Alex Carey joined Cameron Green and they scored runs at a brisk pace. Their hard work has put the visitors in the lead by 21 runs at the moment.

Session Summary - Overs - 27, Runs - 135, Wickets - 2. Australia's session, without a doubt! After the first session of Day 2, the visitors find themselves in a much stronger position. Alex Carey and Cameron Green have made batting look so easy and their unbeaten stand of 76 runs has put Sri Lanka under the pump.
Back-of-a-length delivery on middle, Cameron Green eases it back towards the bowler. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Sticks to bowling it shorter again, Cameron Green ducks under it and lets it through and towards the keeper.
This one lands slightly shorter and on middle, Cameron Green looks to defend it but the ball hits his gloves and rolls towards the off side.
Sticks to bowling it shorter and on middle, Cameron Green ducks under it again.
Shorter one again, Cameron Green ducks underneath it.
Starts with a shorter one on leg, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
Asitha Fernando comes back to bowl. 4-0-28-0 are his figures so far!
Flighted full and on middle, Alex Carey strides forward and defends firmly.
Alex Carey attempts the reverse sweep once again but this time the ball is not as full and towards leg, he manages to get a faint edge that makes the ball go away from the stumps.
Alex Carey comes down the wicket and plays the ball on the full, back towards the bowler.
A mandatory concussion check for Alex Carey as he took a blow on the grille of his helmet. No issues. Smiles all around.

Bang on the helmet! Alex Carey is using the reverse sweep as his go-to shot! This is a fraction shorter outside off, Alex Carey misses the line of the ball as it spins and crashes into the grille of his helmet. If not for the helmet, Carey could have lost his front teeth.
Flighted full once again, Alex Carey paddles this but straight to the short fine leg fielder.

FOUR! Alex Carey has looked wonderful in this innings! Lasith Embuldeniya tosses this one full on off, Alex Carey connects with his reverse sweep powerfully as the ball races to the deep point boundary! He reaches his 40s in no time!
Lasith Embuldeniya is back on. 11-0-58-0 are his dismal figures so far.
FOUR! Goes fuller and down the leg side, Cameron Green uses his feet and flicks it sharply through mid-wicket for a boundary. The lead moves to 17 now.

Shout for an lbw, not given. A googly by Jeffrey Vandersay, it lands on a fuller length around middle and beats the forward defense of Green. It pings him on the pads, they appeal but the umpire stays still. Missing leg. Too much turn there.
Goes outside off again, this is again guided towards deep point for a couple of runs.
Bowls it on middle with some turn, Cameron Green waits for the ball and guides it to deep point for a brace.
This one lands outside off as well, Alex Carey sweeps it towards backward square leg for a single again.
Goes fuller and outside off, Cameron Green drives it towards long off for one.
Jeffrey Vandersay (6-0-33-1) comes back to bowl. He replaces Ramesh Mendis!

FOUR! Alex Carey almost guides this towards the slip fielder! The ball moves away from the batter from a good length, Alex Carey tries to work this fine for a single but gets a thick edge that makes the ball fly closer to the slip fielder than he had anticipated! The slip fielder dives to his left but does not reach it as the ball reaches the boundary to add four runs to the lead!
WIDE! Goes even shorter but on a good line. The square leg umpire says it is too high and wide has been called.
Short delivery this time but wide from off stump. Alex Carey initially shapes up to pull this but changes his mind at the last moment.
Around the wicket to the left-hander, bowled on a good length and angling away, Alex Carey plays this towards gully.
Full once again on middle, Cameron Green gets this wide of mid on for a single.
Fraction fuller this time angling into the pads, Cameron Green flicks this towards the mid-wicket fielder who parries it towards mid on.
Asitha Fernando starts this over well. Good-length delivery angling in from outside off. Cameron Green defends this one back down the pitch.
FOUR! Australia lead by 1 run now. Fuller in length around middle, Alex Carey sits down on one knee and sweeps it firmly through square leg for a boundary.
Tossed-up delivery, Alex Carey looks to sweep at it but misses as the ball goes straight into the gloves of the keeper.
Bowls it on leg and fuller in length, Alex Carey flicks it towards the fielder at backward square leg.
Skidding down the leg side, Alex Carey tries to sweep but misses. He is hit on the pads, they appeal but to no avail.
Lands it on middle and fuller in length, Alex Carey sweeps it but finds the fielder at leg gully.

FOUR LEG BYES! Goes fuller on middle, spinning away from the batter with extra bounce, Alex Carey looks to swing at it but misses. The keeper misses it as well it bounces past his left shoulder. The ball races behind for a boundary. The 50-run stand comes up!
Yorker around off, Green digs it out safely.
Back of a length, around leg, Carey fails to glance and it goes off his thigh pad to square leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Wide! Asitha Fernando digs it in short but it goes way over the head of the batter.
Fuller and on middle, a hint of reverse there as Green flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Cameron Green gets on top of this and defends solidly.
Short delivery angled into the batter. Alex Carey pulls but mistimes it and gets a top edge. The ball falls into the vacant square leg region for a single.

Asitha Fernando goes around the wicket and bowls this full and outside off, Alex Carey hits this hard towards covers. The cover fielder dives to his right and a half stop allows the batters to run two.
Bowls it fuller and on leg, Alex Carey sweeps it towards the square leg for one.
Shorter one outside off, Alex Carey goes on the back foot and cuts it away towards the backward point region.
This one lands on middle and fuller, Cameron Green sweeps it towards backward square leg for one.
Goes fuller down the middle, Cameron Green guides it towards the off side but straight towards the cover fielder.
Another one on middle with some turn, Cameron Green eases it towards the fielder at silly mid on.
Tossed-up delivery on middle, Cameron Green defends it back towards the bowler.
Tad fuller again, outside off. Alex Carey once again drives and finds the fielder at extra-cover. 9 runs off Asitha Fernando's first over on Day 2!
On a length now, outside off. Alex Carey pushes it to the fielder at covers.
FOUR! In the gap this time! Similar delivery pitched up and wide of off. Alex Carey once again creams his drive, through covers, for a boundary.
Another fuller one, outside off. Alex Carey drives again but finds the fielder at the cover region on this occasion.
FOUR! Top shot! Pitches it up, wide of off. Alex Carey drives this uppishly but away from the fielder at covers for a boundary.

Bye! Some swing there for Asitha Fernando! He starts off with a fuller one, swinging down the leg side. Cameron Green looks to flick but he misses. Niroshan Dickwella dives towards his left, but the ball deflects off his left glove and goes towards fine leg. The batters steal a bye!
Close one! Ramesh Mendis this time pulls his length ball, serves a flatter one, around off. Alex Carey stays back and tries to cut this one but he gets an inside edge just away from the leg pole.
Outside off, fuller one. Alex Carey presses forward and defends it towards cover.
Drifting it on the pads. Alex Carey sweeps it towards short fine leg.
Beaten this time! Ramesh Mendis serves this quicker, outside off, full. Alex Carey looks to sweep this one but he fails to get any bat on it this time. That wasn't too far from the off pole.
Outside off, fuller one. Alex Carey leans forward and blocks it towards cover.
There is the sweep again! Tad quicker now, around 87 clicks, tossed up, around the leg pole. Alex Carey hits it through square leg. Asitha Fernando makes a good stop there! Two taken.
Around the off pole, pitches it up. Cameron Green drives but finds the fielder at short cover. Good over for Australia! 11 runs off it.
Slower through the air, full, around middle. Alex Carey tries to sweep this but the ball goes off the top edge over the keeper and towards fine leg. Three taken!
FOUR! Perfectly executed! Tosses this one up, full, around the leg pole. Alex Carey gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps this towards deep cover for a boundary.
Spinning away, a tad shorter, outside off. Cameron Green pushes it through cover for a single.
Around middle and leg on this occasion, full again. Alex Carey gets down on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Good running! Loopy one, full, around middle and off. Alex Carey sticks with his reverse sweep. He gets it away from the fielder at point and takes two runs.
Around off, pitches it up. Cameron Green dances down the track and looks to defend this but the ball goes off the inner half towards mid on.
Another reverse sweep! This time Alex Carey does so to a fuller one away from the slip fielder for a single.
Tad shorter, darting it around the pads. Cameron Green flicks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
Around middle now, full in length. Alex Carey gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps it towards point. Single taken!
Full, around off. Cameron Green once again strokes it to mid off and takes a single this time.
Tosses it up, around off. Cameron Green steps down the pitch and knocks it to Angelo Mathews at mid off. A slight fumble by him there allows the batters to take two runs.

DRINKS! Sri Lanka have struck with two wickets and both the overnight batters have been dismissed but at the same time, Australia scored 71 runs in the last hour. Usman Khawaja reached his half century but could not convert it into a big one. Cameron Green is looking good and will hope that Alex Carey gives him support as they look to reduce the deficit further which is 43 at the moment.
Full, around middle. Alex Carey sweeps it straight to the fielder at short fine leg.
Slower through the air, full, around middle. Cameron Green flicks it through mid-wicket. The ball will not race away and the batters pick up three runs.
Tosses it up, around middle, full in length. Alex Carey tries to sweep this but the ball goes off the top edge and lands in the vacant square leg region. Single taken!
Pitches it up again, outside off, loopy one. Cameron Green advances down once again and drives it towards deep cover for another run.
Tight single there! A fuller one, around middle. Alex Carey gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps this towards point for a quick single.
Tosses this one up, a full toss, around off. Cameron Green steps down the pitch and knocks it down to long off for a single.
Around the wicket this time but still full on the pads, Cameron Green is happy to sweep this towards deep square leg and keep the strike.
Ramesh Mendis goes full and strays down leg. Alex Carey sweeps the ball towards deep square leg for another single.
Jeffrey Vandersay is off the ground, nursing his left thumb which is bleeding. Perhaps, he celebrated too hard. The replays show that he hurt his thumb while stopping the ball in the outfield.
Ramesh Mendis is getting ample turn but the length is short and outside off, Cameron Green has all the time in the world to go back and punch this towards cover for a single.
Alex Carey plays a reverse sweep to get off the mark. Full delivery outside off, Carey plays it towards backward point for a single.
Cameron Green shows good footwork as he comes down the pitch to play a full delivery outside of towards long on for a single.
Fraction short and spinning in from off stump. Cameron Green works this to short mid-wicket.
Alex Carey walks in next. Australia trail by 55 runs.

OUT! TAKEN! Jeffrey Vandersay comes into the attack and strikes straightaway! More importantly, he gets rid of Usman Khawaja here for his maiden Test wicket! Lovely delivery! Tad quicker, fuller one, around middle, Usman Khawaja leans forward and tries to defend this, but the ball spins in and goes off the inside edge towards short leg. Pathum Nissanka reacts quickly and takes a sharp catch diving across to his left.
Commentary.Howout: c Pathum Nissanka b Jeffrey Vandersay

Commentary.Commentary: This one lands on off, Cameron Green shuffles across and guides it towards covers for one.
Bowls it on leg, this is defended out solidly.
Flighted delivery on middle, Usman Khawaja comes down the track and drives it towards deep cover for a single.
This is on off, Green leans backwards and punches it towards deep point for a single.
A low full toss to start with, Usman Khawaja guides it towards long on for one.
Jeffrey Vandersay comes to bowl now.
Short in length, around the middle stump line. Cameron Green defends this firmly back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Usman Khawaja plays this past covers for a single.
Ramesh Mendis bowls this full delivery on off and spins into the batter, Green walks down to defend but only manages to get an inside edge that rolls towards square leg for a single.
Quicker delivery angling in from off stump. Cameron Green works this towards mid-wicket.
Slower delivery, flighted outside off, Usman Khawaja paddles this behind square leg for a single.
It's bowled on a good length outside off. Cameron Green gets back and knocks it towards long on for a single. 150 comes up and the 50-run stand is also notched up by these two batters.
This is similar to the last delivery, Usman Khawaja again defends it back towards Lasith Embuldeniya.
Bowls it on off, Usman Khawaja eases it back towards the bowler.
FOUR BYES! This one lands around leg, Usman Khawaja looks to reverse sweep it but misses. The keeper misses it as well as the ball races behind for a boundary.
Tossed up outside leg, Usman Khawaja walks forward and defends it off the inner half. It lobs up but doesn't carry to short mid-wicket.
Cameron Green gets down the pitch and catches the ball on the full outside off. Drives firmly towards mid off.
FOUR! Cameron Green is looking to be positive against the Sri Lankan spinners! Full delivery on middle stump. Cameron Green gets down and sweeps this with power to the deep square leg boundary!
Slightly back of a length on off, Usman Khawaja goes back and defends this down on the pitch.
Ramesh Mendis continues bowling full, this time on off. Usman Khawaja knocks this towards point.
There is a lot of turn for the spinners here! Ramesh Mendis goes full outside off, the ball turns off the pitch and beats the outside edge of Usman Khawaja who does well not to commit to the shot.
FOUR! Gets under this one! Ramesh Mendis goes full on a middle stump line, Usman Khawaja sees it early and slog-sweeps it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary!
Short and outside off, Usman Khawaja rocks onto his back foot and plays it towards cover-point.
Flighted full on off, Usman Khawaja defends this towards short cover.
Flighted and full, around off, Green gets on the front foot with a big stride and crunches it through covers for a couple of runs.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it back.
Uses his feet this time to a full ball and forces it down to long on for a single.
Tossed up, around off, Usman Khawaja uses the reverse-batted shot and sends it to deep point for a couple of runs.
Goes down on one knee to sweep and bottom-edges it down to short fine leg for a run.

Fires it in, very full and around leg, Green walks forward and pushes it towards silly point. The fielder attempts to have a shy at the striker's end as Cameron returns. The ball hits the striker instead.
Spinning down the leg side, Green helps it towards long leg and takes a single.

FOUR BYES! Another sharp off spinner, around middle, Green advances down the track for a big heave across the line. He misses as it beats the bat and runs wide of the keeper. It finds the fine leg fence.
Gets on the front foot and defends it down.

BIG SHOUT FOR A BAT-PAD! Not given and the Lankans decide not to review. Flighted off spinner, around off and spinning in, Cameron Green walks down the track again but fails to defend. It goes off his pads to short leg. No bat.
Dances down the track to turn it into a full toss and forces it back towards the bowler. Ramesh Mendis mimes a throw.
Spinning down the leg side, Green fails to flick and it goes off his pads to the leg side.
Flatter delivery, outside off, Usman Khawaja walks across the stumps and defends it from the inner half of his blade to short leg.
Flighted around off, Green goes down to take it on the full and sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Gentle spin there, from around off, Green defends it watchfully to covers.
Turning down the leg side, Usman moves back and nudges it to fine leg for a run.
Full again, around middle, Green uses his feet and pushes it down to long off for a single.
Fuller and around off, Green defends it off the front foot.
Quicker one, around off, Green steps down and tries to defend but it takes the outside edge and rolls in the gap at covers. They cross.

SAFE! Floated delivery, landing full around off and spinning back in, Green tries to sweep but misses. He is hit on the flap of the front pad and they appeal. The finger stays down and Sri Lanka opt for the DRS. Nothing on the UltraEdge and the Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the leg stump. Umpire's call.

Review! With 3 seconds left on the timer, Dimuth Karunaratne decides to take a review for an LBW decision against Cameron Green! The replay rolls in and the Ball Tracking indicates that it was the umpire's call on hitting the wickets. The on-field decision stands!
Spinning in from around middle, Green tries to defend but is hit on the pads.
Advances down the track and nearly yorks himself. Somehow digs out the delivery outside off safely.
A bit innovative! Flighted again, full and around off, Khawaja paddle scoops it down towards fine leg for a single.
Extra toss on this delivery as it lands full on off, Khawaja defends it to the off side.
Too full this time, around leg, Green goes down and sweeps it in front of square on the leg side for a brace.
Advances down the track to a full ball and eases knocks it to long on for a single.
Flighted and full, around off, Khawaja takes it on the full and guides it with a reverse-batted shot to third man for two runs.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Oohhh... sharp spin on this occasion. Landing around off and turning back in to cramp the batter for room. Khawaja goes back to cut but only manages to play it out from the inner half of his bat.
Starts with a flighted ball, full and around off, Khawaja defends it in front of his front pad.
Lasith Embuldeniya (7-0-39-0) is brought into the attack.
Sharp spin from around leg, Green tries to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
Quicker one, a touch short again, Green goes on the back foot and defends it down safely.
Short and on off, turning away, Usman goes back and eases it through cover-point for a run.
Fuller and around middle, Green inside-edges his attempted flick through mid-wicket for a single.

Beats everyone. Full and flighted outside off, spinning away, Khawaja attempts to drive lazily at it but misses. It turns and beats first slip as well. They run three byes. The deficit for Australia is under 100 now.
FOUR! In control this time. Fuller and around off, not turning much, Usman Khawaja kneels down and sweeps it firmly to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Turning in from around off, short in length, Green goes deep inside the crease and punches it to sweeper cover for two runs.
Quicker one, around off, defended from the back foot.
FIFTY FOR KHAWAJA! Fuller in length and outside off, Usman Khawaja drives it through covers for a run. It's been hard work for him but Usman has shown the right temperament.
Loopy delivery, full and on off, Usman draws forward in defense.
Skidding in from around off, it's defended back to the bowler.
Soft outside edge. Flighted delivery, full and around off, Usman Khawaja defends it with a loose bottom hand. It goes on the bounce to first slip.
Too full this time, around leg, Khawaja quietly works it to mid-wicket and takes a single. Retains strike and is on 49 now.
Plenty of turn and bounce this time. Around off, Khawaja goes back to defend but it beats his bat.
Loopy and full, around off and spinning away, Usman Khawaja tries to sweep across the line but misses.
Serves it quicker and flatter, around off, Khawaja goes on the back foot and blocks.
Beaten! That's been a common feature of this innings so far. Floated around off, turning away sharply, Khawaja tries to defend the line but is beaten by the spin.
Slightly short and around off, turning in, Green goes on the back foot and works it past mid-wicket for a single.
Identical to the last delivery, once again Khawaja is solid in defense as he leans forward. End of a successful over.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Usman defends it off the front foot.
A touch short and on off, Usman Khawaja is on his back foot as he blocks it back.
Flatter and around middle, skidding down, Khawaja fails to defend and is hit on the pads. Missing leg.
Confident start from Green. Uses his feet to take it on the full and eases it down to long on for a single.
Cameron Green walks out to bat at number 6.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Not a smart choice to play across the line on this surface. Loopy and full, landing around middle and turning away towards off. Travis Head leans across in his stance to flick it against the spin but it takes the leading edge and lobs back towards the bowler. Dhananjaya de Silva reacts to his right and takes a fantastic return catch, diving across to his right. Early success for Sri Lanka. Australia trail by 112 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c & b Dhananjaya de Silva

Commentary.Commentary: It will be spin from the other end as well. Dhananjaya de Silva comes into the attack.

Shout for an lbw, not given. Flighted delivery, full in length and around leg, Travis Head chooses to defend it from the back foot but misses. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but the umpire disagrees. Perhaps, it pitched outside leg. The batters crossed for a leg bye.
Loopy and around off, turning away, Head covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Shortish around off, Head goes back to cut but finds point.
Beaten! That's the length. Fuller and around off, drifting in as it lands. Travis Head lunges to defend but is beaten by the away spin.
Slightly short and on off, Khawaja goes back and plays it down to cover-point for a run.
Begins with a floated delivery, full and around middle, turning away a bit, Khawaja defends it from the outer half of his bat to point.

Finally, after a long wait, we are ready for some action on Day 2! The umpires have made their way out to the middle. The Sri Lankan players are out on the field as well. Usman Khawaja and Travis Head will resume their batting for Australia. Ramesh Mendis will begin the proceedings with the ball. Let's go!

UPDATE - 12.36 pm IST (7.06 am GMT) - We have good news, folks! The covers are being taken off and there is sunshine for the first time today. Let's hope we get some action soon.

UPDATE - 12.20 pm IST (6.50 am GMT) - No positive news till now, the rain continues to pour down but it's on-and-off in nature. On the brighter side, the winds have eased up a bit. Let's hope we get some good news soon. Fingers crossed!

Talking about Rangana Herath in the previous paragraph, let's have a look at the number of wickets he took in the 2016 Test series. He took a total of 28 wickets at an average of 12.75. He grabbed 9 in the first match, 6 in the second, and 13 in the final Test match. It's fair to say, the current Sri Lankan spinners are finding it tough to match his class. In this ongoing Test, Ramesh Mendis, and Jeffrey Vandersay have bowled at an economy of over 3 while Lasith Embuldeniya has bowled over 5. Clearly, the control is not there for now, but there is always hope on this helpful surface.

The waiting game for all of us continues, but let's rewind to the past and see what happened the last time Australia visited Sri Lanka! Australia had toured Sri Lanka back in 2016! It was a long tour, as they played 3 Test matches, 5 ODIs, and 2 T20Is. The visitors absolutely dominated the shorter formats. They clinched the ODI series 4-1, with George Bailey winning the Player of the Series award. They clean swept Sri Lanka 2-0 in the T20I series. Glenn Maxwell was awarded the Player of the Series then. But before the white-ball cricket, the two sides collided in the longest format of the game. There the visitors were handed a 3-0 defeat by Sri Lanka. The heroics of Rangana Herath helped the hosts complete this whitewash. Undoubtedly, he was named the Player of the Series and his class and control are missing in the current spin department, as we witnessed last evening.

UPDATE - 10.51 am IST (5.21 am GMT) - As we still wait for the inspection, here is a tweet from Roshan Abeysinghe - 'The rain has ceased but the winds in Galle is gale force. The start of day quite a long way away.' Not promising signs. Let's stay positive.

While we continue to wait for the start of the game, an interesting fact! Nathan Lyon grabbed his first five-fer on his Test debut at Galle in Sri Lanka way back in 2011. Eleven years later, Lyon still continues to be a real threat. We witnessed him take his 20th five-fer on Day 1 against the same opposition. Nine out of those 20 five-wicket hauls have come in Asia as he equalled the legendary Shane Warne's record of taking the most fifers in Asia (visiting bowlers in the continent). GOAT for a reason!

UPDATE - 9.53 am IST (4.23 am GMT) - A slight ray of hope, folks! It's not raining at the moment, but the wind continues to be intense. However, there has been a lot of water collected on the covers. There is an inspection set to take place at 10.45 am IST (5.15 am GMT). We will keep you updated!

UPDATE - 9.30 am IST (4.00 am GMT) - We witnessed a full day of cricket without any interruptions on Day 1. But unfortunately, the live visuals from the stadium show that there is a slight drizzle at the moment and the conditions are quite windy as well. The whole ground is covered and we are hearing that the wind is so intense that a small stand has just collapsed. Let's hope the weather clears up soon and we begin on time. Stay tuned...

Sri Lanka on the other hand need wickets and they need them quickly. They have 114 runs still in the bank and they have to make sure Australia do not run away with a big lead. Just like on Day 1, we can expect the spinners to play a crucial role once again. Let's see what we have in store in the first session of Day 2. Stay tuned!

Australia put on a clinical performance with the ball. They bundled out Sri Lanka for just 212. It was their spinners, Nathan Lyon and Mitchell Swepson who demolished the Sri Lankan batting lineup as they grabbed 8 wickets between them, with Nathan Lyon picking yet another five-fer. Coming to bat, they lost three wickets, but Usman Khawaja is looking solid at the moment. He along with Travis Head will want to bat deep and stitch a big partnership.

Hello and welcome back folks! It’s time for the second day of this first Test between Sri Lanka and Australia to get underway. We witnessed an intriguing Day 1 of this Test. A total of 13 wickets fell and it's Australia who have their noses slightly ahead in this game so far. Having said that, we can’t count Sri Lanka out completely. A few early wickets and they will be right on top.

That's all we have from the opening day of this Test match. 13 wickets fell, 10 belonging to the spinners and we are expecting this trend to continue on Thursday as well. The first ball on Day 2 will be at 10 am IST (4.30 am GMT) but you can join us in advance for the build-up. Until then, it's goodbye and cheers!

Earlier in the morning, Dimuth Karunaratne won the all-important toss but his decision to bat first was not ably backed by his players. They started well in the first hour but then two needless shots resulted in two wickets. Thereafter, the Australian spinners turned on the heat in the afternoon session with Nathan Lyon and Mitchell Swepson making full use of the helpful conditions. Just when the chips were down and surviving appeared next to impossible, Niroshan Dickwella walked in. 'Attack is the best form of defense' - Dickwella pulled out that old cliche from the closet and his fresh and positive approach gave wings to the Lankan innings. Although, despite his efforts, the home team put up only 212 runs on the board.

It was a rollicking start from Australia. The tourists amassed 47 runs from the first 9 overs as the Lankan spinners struggled. They bowled poor lines, poor lengths, too many boundary balls and there was no pressure exerted. Ramesh Mendis eventually struck some rhythm to remove David Warner and Marnus Labuschagne and they got a bonus run out to get rid of Steven Smith. Usman Khawaja is still out there, fighting out with his newly found technique against the spinners and he will have to keep that run out behind him quickly. If Australia manage to bat with authority on Day 2, not just this Test match, they will gain the momentum for the rest of the series.

A day that has belonged to the spinners comes to an end! There was no change in the script, we expected this Test match to be dominated by the spinners and that's happening. We would have called it Australia's day but they lost a couple of wickets too many, still, you can say that they are slightly ahead in this Test match. They trail by 114 runs and can put themselves in an advantageous position if they bat sensibly on Day 2. Sri Lanka would be ruing those missed stumping chances, against both the current batters, had Niroshan Dickwella collected the ball, the hosts would have been on top at the close of the day's play.

Usman Khawaja takes the single off the last ball of the day and will take the strike on the morning of Day 2! This is a bit quicker and flatter on middle, Usman Khawaja just nudges it towards square leg and takes an easy single. That will be Stumps on Day 1!
Shorter in length again, around off. Usman Khawaja goes back again to defend it comfortably.
On the shorter side, around off. Usman Khawaja lets it turn and defends it towards the off side off the back foot.
Pulls his length back slightly, around off. Usman Khawaja defends it towards silly point.
Pushes it quicker on middle. This is a front-foot defense off the middle of the blade.
Lands on middle and turns away slightly. Usman Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
On the shorter side, on off. Usman Khawaja goes back and punches it to covers for a single.

There is that perfect length, just short of full length. Pitches it around off and Usman Khawaja looks to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball turns and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Tossed up on off and fuller in length. Usman Khawaja drives it back to the bowler.
This is turning away after pitching on off and Usman Khawaja blocks it off the back foot.
Slower through the air and a lot more air given to it as well, on middle. Usman Khawaja is solid on his front-foot defense.
Quicker and flatter on off. Usman Khawaja goes back and blocks it out.
Steven Smith is still looking upset, sitting in the dressing room. He loves to bat but first injuries kept him out of a few games of the shorter version and now this run out. Poor chap.
Good over that from Dhananjaya de Silva! Tossed up nicely on off again. Not enough full for Head to drive so he settles with a front foot defence.
An arm ball this time on middle. Usman Khawaja works it to square leg for a single.
Nicely bowled. Flighted delivery, outside off. Usman Khawaja pushes it gently towards the off side.
Tossed up on middle. Usman Khawaja pushes it back to the bowler.
This is bowled a bit outside off, Usman Khawaja makes a good block off the front foot again.
Slower through the air on off, Usman Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Dhananjaya de Silva is into the attack now with two lefties in the middle.

Wow! Beaten again! Loopy delivery, around off. Head looks to defend it off the front foot but the ball turns and beats the outside edge of his blade. Dickwella behind the stumps fails to collect the ball cleanly.
Shorter and outside off. Head punches it to covers.

Stumping chance, missed again! Loopy and full, around off, Head walks forward and tries to work it away but misses. It goes to the keeper with extra bounce and again Niroshan Dickwella fails to collect the ball. He is hit on the shoulder and the ball deflects away. Head returns.
Tossed up on middle. Usman Khawaja drives it to long on for a single.
An arm ball angling into middle. Head works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Just short of the first slip fielder! Drifting in on off and turns away. Head looks to defend but gets the outside edge and the ball falls short of Dhananjaya de Silva at first slip.
FOUR! Nicely played! Finds the gap perfectly! Jeffrey Vandersay pitches it outside off and it turns into Usman Khawaja. He reverse-sweeps it through the backward point region for a boundary.
Shortish delivery on middle. Head uses the depth of his crease and works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Goes fuller on middle. Usman Khawaja works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Usman Khawaja skips down the track and yorks himself in the process. He digs it out towards the off side.
Pushes it quicker and flatter on off. Usman Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Head drives it to long on as he beats the diving effort from the bowler, for a single.
Unplayable. Drifting in from around off, and turning away, Khawaja attempts to defend but in vain. Top over by Mendis.

APPEAL FOR STUMPING! Niroshan Dickwella is not showing much confidence though. Floated and full, close to off and spinning away, Khawaja gets forward to drive but misses. Dickwella breaks the stumps and appeals. The third umpire is referred. He first checks for the outside edge and it's absent. The side-on angle then shows that Khawaja had his back leg inside the crease.
Spinning away from outside off, Head goes back to cut but edges it down to third man for three runs.
Turning square, from around off, Head tries to defend but is beaten.
Floated and full, around off, defended off the front foot.
Travis Head walks out next.

OUT! RUN OUT! Steven Smith is livid with his partner. This is a bonus wicket for Sri Lanka and a body blow to Australia. A loopy delivery, full and around leg, Smith skips down the track to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to covers as the bowler puts in an unsuccessful appeal. Smith sees at his partner and steps forward for a run. Usman Khawaja responds but then stops abruptly. Smudge has no way to go. He tries to scoot back but the throw from the fielder (Kusal Mendis) comes to the keeper and he dislodges the bails. The full-length dive is also not enough. Smith returns shaking his head.
Commentary.Howout: run out (Niroshan Dickwella / Kusal Mendis)

Commentary.Commentary: BIG APPEAL! It's for a caught behind down the leg side but the umpire shakes his head. Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the referral as Niroshan Dickwella convinces him. Full and around leg, spinning down, Khawaja tries to flick but seems to have missed it. Niroshan Dickwella collects and jumps in appeal. The DRS is taken and the UltraEdge shows a flat line. A review wasted.
Slower through the air, around middle and turning in, Khawaja goes on the back foot and defends it in front of his pads.
Quicker this time, full and around leg, Smith nudges it to mid on and picks up another run.
Loopy and full, around off, Usman walks forward and eases it down to long on for a run.
Too full this time, outside off, Smith strokes it through covers and picks up a single.
Loopy leg spinner, landing outside off, Smith allows it through to the keeper.
Around off, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Loopy and full, around off, Smith jumps down the track and puts his bat and pad together in defense. It goes off his pads to covers and they cross. Given as a run. Maybe, some inside edge.
Fuller and on off, spinning in, Smith leans forward and defends it from the inner half to mid-wicket.
Shortish and close to off, Usman Khawaja goes back and hits it to point for a single.
Uses his feet this time and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Shout for an lbw, not given. Turn and bounce, from middle, Smith offers no shot and wears it on his pads. They appeal but it's easily going down the leg side.
Quicker and fuller around leg, Khawaja flicks but finds the mid-wicket fielder. A decent first over in Test cricket for Jeffrey Vandersay.
Floated and on off, it's defended solidly off the front foot.
Turning down the leg side, Usman Khawaja goes back to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to leg gully.
Flatter through the air, around off and turning in, Khawaja goes on the back foot in defense.
Finds the gap with his drive and sends it to sweeper cover for a single.
Flighted and full, outside off, Smith drives it to covers.

Mandatory concussion test for Niroshan Dickwella! He has been hit on the helmet on the previous delivery. It is a soft blow though and he looks fine to resume. Jeffrey Vandersay is into the attack now.

STUMPING CHANCE MISSED! Sri Lanka could have got two wickets in the over. Loopy delivery, drifting in around off and turning away, Usman Khawaja gives the charge, aiming for a big shot down the ground but is beaten by the spin. Niroshan Dickwella fails to collect the ball as he is hit on the helmet and Khawaja rushes back. This is poor thinking from Khawaja, they have lost a wicket in the over and there is no need to do anything reckless.
Quicker and shorter again, around off, Usman Khawaja defends from the back foot.
Flatter and around off, defended off the back foot.
Fuller and around off, Smith walks forward and bunts it to mid on for a quick run. Opens his account.
Steven Smith is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Marnus has gifted his wicket away here. Poor from the young man. Completely needless. Sri Lanka were under pressure and he has offered them a new lease of life. Flighted delivery, full and around middle, Marnus Labuschagne goes down for the reverse-batted sweep shot, fails to keep it down as it takes the top half of his blade and it goes straight into the hands of Asitha Fernando at backward point. He makes no mistake and Sri Lanka have two wickets in the kitty now. Australia trail by 137 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Asitha Fernando b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary.Commentary: Sharp spin from around off, on a fuller length, Marnus defends it at the last moment from the back foot. Should have been forward.
A touch flatter this time, around off, Khawaja gets across the stumps to cover the line and defends it down. 9 from the over, Lasith Embuldeniya has gone for 39 runs in his 7 overs so far. Dismal.
Fullish and around middle, Labuschagne sweeps it to deep mid-wicket, this time gets only a run.
Slightly short and on off, Marnus Labuschagne punches it from the back foot to cover-point.
FOUR! Another great shot! Very full and around off, Marnus Labuschagne gets down on one knee and sweeps it sweetly through mid-wicket. There is a fielder in the deep but he is a mere spectator.
Full and floated, around off, spinning away, Marnus Labuschagne leaves.
FOUR! Superbly played! Fuller in length, around leg, Marnus Labuschagne goes down for the sweep shot and hammers it to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Play and a miss! A touch short but too close to off, Khawaja attempts to cut and is beaten.
Tossed up, around leg, Usman Khawaja goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Lunges to a full ball outside off and defends it watchfully.

FOUR! Fine shot! Flighted again, but this time it's short in length and around off, Khawaja camps back and crunches it past the point fielder for a boundary. The Lankan spinners continue to leak boundary balls every over.
Turn and bounce from around off, Khawaja goes back to cover his stumps and then lets it be.
Fuller in length and around leg, Khawaja steps forward and works it in the gap at mid-wicket for two.

Drinks break. Australia have started their innings on a positive note but Lanka would be happy to get rid of Warner who was looking quite dangerous. Sri Lanka need to tighten things up and build pressure on the batters with consistent lines and lengths, they have been off target so far and Dimuth Karunaratne would hope for a better performance from his spinners from hereon. Marnus Labuschagne has joined Usman Khawaja in the middle and he would be looking to get a good score under his belt, something he has not done in the subcontinent conditions consistently.
Loopy and full, around middle, Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and defends it back to end the over.
Fullish and close to off, Marnus pushes it off the front foot to covers.
Too full in length, drifting in around leg, Marnus Labuschagne defends it back.
Flighted and full around middle, Usman Khawaja knocks it down to long on and rotates the strike.
Khawaja comes down the track and makes the length very full. He, then, drills it down to long off. The long on fielder circles around it in the deep and the batters get two runs.
Fuller and around off, defended off the front foot.
Flighted and outside off, turning away, Khawaja gets forward and opens the face of his bat late. He guides it past backward point and collects a single.
Beauty to beat the bat! Slower through the air, full and around off, Khawaja tries to defend the line of the delivery but it spins away to beat the bat. It misses the top of off by a whisker.
FOUR! Slapped away! Short this time, around off, Khawaja uses the depth of his crease and cracks it past the point fielder for a boundary.
Slower through the air, full and outside off, Khawaja drives but finds the cover-point fielder.
Loopy and full around off, Marnus Labuschagne slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket for a single.
Floated delivery, full and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne comes down the track and helps it to mid-wicket.
Loopy and full around middle, Khawaja defends it off the front foot. A much-better over from Embuldeniya.
Uses his feet to a full ball around off and drives it to wide mid off.

A dipping full delivery around off, Marnus Labuschagne reaches out and tries to take it on the full. It takes the inner portion as Marnus tries to sweep and runs down to deep backward square leg. They cross.
Advances down the track to a full ball and defends it safely.
Flatter and a touch shorter, around off, Marnus Labuschagne goes back and punches it to the right of the cover-point fielder.
Too full in length, around middle, Marnus defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up nicely on off. Usman Khawaja drives it to extra cover.
On middle and turning in. Marnus Labuschagne nudges it behind square on the leg side for a single. 50 up!

Shorter and outside off. Usman Khawaja punches it off the back foot towards point. They go for a quick single and the fielder at point has a shy at the bowler's end. He misses and a run is completed easily in the end.
On middle and fuller. Marnus Labuschagne sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Marnus Labuschagne skips down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Marnus Labuschagne walks in next, at number 3. Australia trail by 165 runs.

OUT! LBW! Ramesh Mendis strikes and David Warner doesn't even bother to take the review! The natural variation for an off spinner is on display. Ramesh Mendis pitches it around off and it skids on after landing to beat the forward defense of Warner. He is rapped on the back leg and there is an appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Warner backs back disappointed. Sri Lanka needed this breakthrough! Perhaps, Warner was playing for the away spin as the seam of the ball suggested but it went on with the angle and brought his downfall.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary.Commentary: Slower through the air on middle, Warner drives it straight down the ground. The fielder at long on cuts it off. A single taken.
Reaches the pitch of the ball and works this full delivery on middle to long on for a single.
Angling into leg. Usman Khawaja blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Sri Lanka have been very inconsistent with their lines and lengths! Overpitched outside off, Usman Khawaja leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Angling into leg. Usman Khawaja tucks it fine towards the fine leg region for a couple.
Beaten! This is pushed quicker and outside off. It is slightly short as well and Usman Khawaja goes back to push inside the line. The ball ends up beating the outside edge of his blade.
Shorter in length on middle. Warner pulls from the back foot but finds the mid-wicket fielder.

An appeal for LBW but Warner was way down the pitch there! A flatter delivery on middle, Warner skips down the track but ends up getting hit on the pads as he looks to defend. There is an appeal but the umpire is not interested.
It is fuller and outside off again. Usman Khawaja drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Usman Khawaja makes a good leave.

Given lbw! Usman Khawaja refers the decision immediately. Flighted delivery, full and around leg and it straightens from there. Khawaja tries to flick but misses. He is pinged on the pads, they appeal and the finger goes up after a short while. DRS is taken. Bat is absent on the UltraEdge but it's PITCHING OUTSIDE LEG as per the Ball Tracking. The onfield decision has been overturned.
Bowls a yorker on middle, it drifts into the batter and Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Goes fuller on middle. Usman Khawaja skips down the track and works it to long on for a single.
Turning in from around off, Khawaja helps it with the spin to mid-wicket.
A flatter one on middle. Usman Khawaja blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This is tossed up, outside off. Usman Khawaja reaches to the pitch of the ball with a big stride and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Walks forward to a full ball and blocks again.
Flighted and full, around off, defended.
Tossed up on off. Warner blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Well played! This is again fuller and angling into middle and leg. Warner sweeps it through the square leg region, in the gap, for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, Warner drives it to mid on.
On the shorter side on middle. Usman Khawaja works it behind square on the leg side for a single.

Huge appeal but the umpire says no. Sri Lanka do not take a review as Ramesh Mendis signals that Usman Khawaja got a bat on it. Tossed up, very full and on middle, Usman Khawaja looks to reverse sweep but only manages to get a faint part of his blade to the back thigh.
Flighted delivery on off. Usman Khawaja defends it back to the bowler.
Goes a tad short and it turns towards off, Warner goes back and blocks it out.
Lasith Embuldeniya goes fuller on middle. Usman Khawaja flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Short and turning down the leg side. Usman Khawaja looks to pull but misses.
Shorter in length on middle. Usman Khawaja works it to short leg.
Keeps it fuller on middle. Warner reaches the pitch of the ball, and plays it with the turn to long on for a single.
This is full on off. Usman Khawaja drives it to long on for a single.
Four different bowlers have bowled the first four overs. Will we see another change? Nopes, Lasith Embuldeniya will continue...
Goes tad fuller on middle. Warner pushes it towards the leg side.
Much better! Lands it around off. It is nicely tossed up and then turns away to beat the outside edge of Warner's blade.
This is on leg. Usman Khawaja paddles it to fine leg and the batters take three. Good running between the wickets.
Pushes it quicker on off, Usman Khawaja probably goes back to a delivery that he could have gone forward but manages to block it in the end.
Angles it into leg this time. Warner sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Nicely bowled! Drifting into middle and turns a tad as Warner defends it off the front foot.
Dimuth Karunaratne is ringing in the changes. Ramesh Mendis comes into the attack as well.
Same line and the same length. David Warner skips down the track and hits it down the ground this time. The fielder at long on cuts it off and a single is taken.
Another very full delivery, targeting the stumps. Warner plays it back to the bowler again.
Keeps it very full on middle. Warner drives it back to the bowler.
NO BALL! Tossed up on middle. Warner flicks it to mid-wicket. Lasith Embuldeniya has overstepped here. He is a habitual offender.
A fuller delivery on off, Warner skips down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Warner is dealing in boundaries at the moment! Lasith Embuldeniya keeps it short and around off. Warner uses the depth of the crease and punches it through cover-point for a boundary.

FOUR! David Warner greets Lasith Embuldeniya with a boundary! It is short and outside off, Warner rocks back and cuts it in front of square on the off side for a boundary. The deficit is below 200 now.
That's it from Asitha Fernando then. Here comes Lasith Embuldeniya, the most experienced spin bowler in the Lankan XI. ​David Warner, wearing a floppy hat, is ready to face the challenge...
On the shorter side again, around off. Usman Khawaja waits for it and punches it to covers.
Slightly shorter on off. Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on off. Usman Khawaja skips down the track and hits it straight to short cover.
Fuller and around off. Warner knocks it down to long off for a single.
This comes in with the angle, on middle, Warner defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Usman Khawaja drives it to the right of mid off for a single.
As expected, we have a spinner from the other end. It's Dhananjaya de Silva, not the one from the trio of genuine spinners that Sri Lanka have opted for!

FOUR! Two in two for Warner! This is hit even harder. He probably wants to get as many runs as possible before the spinners get into action. Poor delivery this, short and wide outside off. Warner cuts and cuts it hard through point this time for a boundary.
FOUR! Warner is off the mark in style! Short and outside off, Warner rocks back and cuts it through covers firmly for a boundary.
Drifting on the pads. Usman Khawaja clips it to fine leg for a single. Australia and Usman Khawaja are underway!
Lovely delivery! Serves a good length delivery, around off. It nips away this time and beats the outside edge of Usman Khawaja's blade as he looks to defend.
Lands on a length, on middle and it nips back in. Usman Khawaja looks to clip it away but misses. He gets hit high on his pads.
Asitha Fernando starts with a back-of-a-length delivery on off, and Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
We are back for Australia's reply. The Lankan players are out in the middle. David Warner and Usman Khawaja are the openers for Australia. Ramesh Mendis to start with the ball.
...FOURTH INNINGS...

Sri Lanka scored 17 runs in this first over and it seemed like they will go with the aggressive route throughout but that was not the case. Once the spinners were introduced, there was no comeback for the hosts as no one showed any determination and fell into the trap one after the other. Now then, Australia need 5 runs to win! Big deal! Stay tuned as we will be back in a bit!

Take a moment and appreciate that spell from the 'GOAT', Nathan Lyon. He bowled from one end throughout the session and he was the one who started the downfall of Sri Lanka. He in tandem with Mitchell Swepson showed their spin magic and the Lankan batters were really feeling the heat against them. Travis Head came out of the syllabus as well. His spell of (2.5-0-10-4) just showed it was a classical spin bowling which was a route to bundle the opposition.

What a spell that was from the Aussie spinners. A spell which the great Shane Warne and Muttiah Muralitharan will be really proud of! On the other hand, it was an abysmal batting show from Sri Lanka. This is also, the lowest number of overs Sri Lanka has ever faced in an innings.

OUT! LBW! That is it for the Sri Lankan innings. This one was full and on middle and leg, Embuldeniya tries to flick it but gets beaten and gets hit on his pads. The Australians appeal for the LBW but the finger stayed down. Pat Cummins goes for the review and it works in their favour, as the Ball Tracking shows three reds to end this Sri Lankan innings. Travis Head steals the spotlight here with his 4-fer in just 2.5 overs.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Travis Head

Commentary.Commentary: Full and on the middle, Embuldeniya blocks it off.
On a length and on middle, Fernando smears it to mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Asitha Fernando manages to get some lead on board now with this boundary. Tossed up on the off, Fernando just smashes it over the bowler for a boundary at long on. Incredible hit but comes a little too late.
Asitha Fernando is the last man in. Sri Lanka still trail by 1 run.

OUT! BOWLED! What a beauty of a delivery. This one lands on the rough outside off, turns sharply into the right hander. Vandersay tries to play a drive at it but the ball goes between his bat and pads and hits top of middle stump.
Commentary.Howout: b Travis Head

Commentary.Commentary: Nathan Lyon bowls it on middle, Lasith Embuldeniya blocks it solidly.
This one lands on off and turns sharply, Lasith Embuldeniya looks to defend it but misses.
Fuller one on middle, Lasith Embuldeniya defends it soolidly off his front foot.
On off, Lasith Embuldeniya looks to play at it but misses.
Lasith Embuldeniya walks in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tossed up on middle, Niroshan Dickwella looks to reverse sweep it but gets a top edge and the ball carries towards short cover where Labuschagne takes a diving catch with both hands to his left. Australia are looking to bag Sri Lanka before Lunch.
Commentary.Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up on leg, Jeffrey Vandersay sweeps it but gets a top edge. The ball was in the air for some time but falls in no man's land at short fine leg. They rotate the strike.
Fuller, on middle and off. Niroshan Dickwella tries to sweep it away but misses. Head appeals but the umpire is unmoved. It clearly hits his gloves, the replays later confirm.
Full length and on the off, Vandersay crunches it past the cover fielder. They take three runs.
On a length and on off, Vandersay drives it straight to mid off.
Full and on the middle, Vandersay tries to play the reverse sweep but finds the man at backward point.
BYES! Misses everyone. This land outside off, and turns in sharply. Jeffrey Vandersay fails to get any blade on it. Carey fails to gather it and the batters sneak in a couple.
On a length outside off, turning away, Dickwell cuts it past point for a single.
FOUR! Tossed-up delivery, Jeffrey Vandersay reverse sweeps it towards deep point for a boundary.
Shorter on middle, Jeffrey Vandersay punches it towards covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Huge trouble for the hosts as Ramesh Mendis walks out on a duck! Fuller with a hint of turn, Ramesh Mendis looks to sweep it but gets a top edge as the ball carries towards fine leg and Usman Khawaja takes a comfortable catch. They trail by 12 now. Jeffrey Vandersay is the new man in.
Commentary.Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: On middle, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it towards backward square leg  for one.
Fuller on middle and turns it sharply, Niroshan Dickwella looks to sweep again but misses.
Fuller on leg, Niroshan Dickwella looks to sweep it but could not connect well.
On off, blocked out. What a change by Pat Cummins. Head literally turned this game on his head. Two crucial wickets in the over. Sri Lanka in huge trouble.
Ramesh Mendis walks out to the middle.

OUT! LBW! Another man bites the dust for Sri Lanka. The umpire wasn't interested at first but is forced to change his decision here. It is looped up, around off, turning in. Dhananjaya de Silva misjudges it completely. He goes deep inside his crease and leaves it alone thinking it would go down leg, although it straightens a touch and causes a lot of trouble. Pat Cummins opts for the review. No UltraEdge is required. The Ball Tracking shows three reds.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Travis Head

Commentary.Commentary: A stifled appeal from the bowler. Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and blocks it out.
A loud appeal from behind the sticks but the bowler shows no interest. It is full and angled down leg. Niroshan Dickwella gets low and sweeps it to short fine leg for one. There is some nick on it.
Niroshan Dickwella comes in. He scored a half-century in the first innings and needs to do something similar here.

OUT! BOWLED! This one turns sharply in from outside off, Chandimal goes for the drive as the ball sneaks in between his pads and the bat and hits the middle pole. The hosts have now lost half of their side and they look to be in deep trouble.
Commentary.Howout: b Travis Head

Commentary.Commentary: Head starts with a length delivery on the off, turning in. Dinesh Chandimal plays a front foot defense.
Mitchell Swepson gets a rest from his spell as Travis Head will replace him.
Tossed-up delivery, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards mid on for one.
FOUR! Fuller on off, Dinesh Chandimal plays a reverse sweep as the ball goes behind the backward point fence for a boundary.
On off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to play at it but gets an inside edge and hits his pads.
This one lands on off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to reverse sweep it but gets a bottom edge and rolls towards the leg slip.
On off, this is pushed towards point for one.

Oh, close again. This was shorter and on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to play at it but the ball hits his glove and falls short from the keeper who chases it. Nathan Lyon is causing havoc for Sri Lanka with his sharp turn and bounce.
Short and wide on off, Chandimal goes on his back foot and cuts it sweetly but could not get it past the cover fielder.
This one lands on middle and leg, Chandimal drives it straight to mid on.
On a length and on off, de Silva pushes it to the off side for a single.
Loopy fulltoss on the middle, de Sliva drives it hard straight towards the bowler, but it did not carry.
On length on the leg,turning a bit. de Silva lets it hit his body.
Tossed up on the off, Chandimal uses his feet to drive it to mid off and gets a quick single.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Dhananjaya de Silva eases it towards the fielder at short leg.
Touch fuller and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off, Dinesh Chandimal reverse sweeps it towards backward point for one.
Shorter one on off, Dhananjaya de Silva cuts it through point for three runs.
On off, this is defended out solidly.
FOUR BYES! Fuller and outside leg, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to flick it but misses as the ball races to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full delivery on the middle, Chandimal defends it solidly.
A bit short on the off, Chandimal plays a cut off his back foot but could only find the fielder at point.
Full and on the middle, Dhananjaya de Silva plays a slogsweep towards deep square leg. They get across for a single.
Length and outside off, turning away. Chandimal knocks it towards third man for a single.
On a length and on off, turning away, Chandimal blocks it out.
Length delivery outside off, turning away. Chandimal plays a cut off his back foot past the point fielder for a brace.
Fuller in length, Dhananjaya de Silva uses his feet and pushes it to covers.

FOUR BYES! This was a chance for stumping but the keeper misses it. This one lands outside off and turns in sharply, Dhananjaya de Silva dances down the track to play at it but misses. The keeper also misses it as it races down to the fine leg fence.
This one lands outside off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to cut it but gets a bottom edge and bounces through the wicket and past the fielder. They take a single.
On off this time, Dinesh Chandimal guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
Fuller and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it back towards the bowler.

FOUR LEG BYES! This one lands outside off and turns in, Dinesh Chandimal looks to reverse sweep it but misses. The keeper misses it as well as the ball races towards the long stop and behind the fence for a boundary.
Sharp Turn! Good-length delivery, turning away from the right hander, Dhananjaya de Silva decides to leave it alone.
Full again and on the leg, Chandimal gets down and plays an uppish sweep to the deep square leg fielder for a single.
This one lands a bit short, turning in, de Silva pushes it to deep backward cover for a single.
Full toss around leg, Chandimal gets off the mark with a sweep towards fine leg.
Dinesh Chandimal walks out now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mitchell Swepson is already celebrating, the fielders around join in as well. Although the umpire takes his time to raise the finger. The umpires have a chat and decide to go upstairs to check the bump ball. The soft signal is out. The replays show clear spike as the ball passes the blade. Coming to the delivery, it is full and outside off, Fernando tries to dig it out but gets an outside edge and it goes to first slip where Steven Smith takes a sharp catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Steven Smith b Mitchell Swepson

Commentary.Commentary: Is that out? There is an outside edge but it is referred upstairs to check if it is a bump ball. Soft signal is out. Oshada Fernando stands his ground. The replay shows there was a thick outside edge as confirmed by Ultra Edge. Out it is!
Tossed up and on the leg, Dhananjaya de Silava drives it towards long on. They get 3 runs.

Halt in play! Marnus Labuschagne at short leg gets hit on the helmet and he has to go through a mandatory concussion test. He looks fine but looks like he needs a breather as he is seen walking off the field.

Oh, this was close! This one lands on leg, Oshada Fernando sweeps it but the ball hits the helmet of the fielder at short leg and just falls short of Nathan Lyon who makes a diving effort. Oshada Fernando gets a lucky escape.
This was similar to the last delivery, Oshada Fernando again defends it towards Nathan Lyon.
Goes on off, Oshada Fernando defends it away.
This one lands on leg, Dhananjaya de Silva sweeps it towards the leg side for one.
On off and turns it a long way, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to block it but the ball hits his pads. A slight appeal but the umpire seems uninterested.

Drinks! Other than the first couple of overs, everything is going downhill for Sri Lanka! They have started to succumb against the spin and are losing wickets in a flurry. Australia will be really happy at the moment. Lyon is showing his experience yet again as he grabbed a couple already and will look to continue the good work. Sri Lanka trail by 50 runs. Also, Dhananjaya de Silva is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tossed up on middle with some turn, Kusal Mendis looks to sweep it but gets a top edge as the ball carries towards short fine leg. Mitchell Swepson makes no mistake and takes a comfortable catch in his both hands. Huge trouble for Sri Lanka as they lose their third wicket! They still trail by 50 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Mitchell Swepson b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Full and on the leg, Fernando flicks it but could not find the gap.
A bit short outside off, Fernando pushes it to point.
SIX! Lovely Shot. This was tossed up on the middle, Fernando clears his back leg and just lofts it through the line over the bowlers head for a biggie.
Tossed up on the leg, flicked to short mid-wicket.
Full and on the middle, Fernando blocks it straight to the bowler.
Full and on the off, turning away, Mendis leans forward and drives to point for a quick single.
Dropped! Fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis flicks it and hits it straight to Warner who gets both hands to it but fails to catch it.
Flighted delivery on leg, Oshada Fernando steps out and looks to go over mid on but miscues it towards deep mid wicket. The ball fell short of the fielder and they take a single.
Turning in on middle, Oshada Fernando leaves it and it brushes his pads and rolls towards the leg slip.

An appeal but the finger stays down. Fuller and turning it on the leg, Oshada Fernando looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his pads. There was big turn and the replay shows it was umpire's call on wickets hitting.
Oh, this was close. Fuller and on middle, Oshada Fernando flicks it towards mid on. The ball carries but just falls short of the fielder at mid on. Oshada Fernando gets a lucky breakthrough.
Fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis sweeps it but finds the fielder at backward square leg. They take a single.
Tosses it up on middle, Kusal Mendis looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards the leg side. They take a single.
Much fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller in length and on middle, Oshada Fernando works it towards the leg side for a single.
This is outside off again, Oshada Fernando defends it away.
Goes outside off, Oshada Fernando looks to sweep again but misses it this time.
FOUR! This one lands outside leg, Oshada Fernando uses the pace of the ball and sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Tossed-up delivery, this is guided towards the off side.
Fuller and outside off, Kusal Mendis looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces back towards the keeper.
This one lands on leg, Kusal Mendis defends it towards short leg fielder.
Fuller on off with some tun, Kusal Mendis looks to play at it but misses.
Guides a fuller ball towards the fielder at point.
FOUR! Tossed up on middle, Kusal Mendis gets on his knees and sweeps it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, defended out.
Oshada Fernando comes in at number 4.

OUT! LBW! A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Pathum Nissanka decides to go upstairs. A flighted delivery on the stumps, Nissanka gets down on one knee and looks to sweep it but misses as the ball hits his thigh. Ball Tracking shows that the ball was hitting the stumps and Pathum Nissanka has to walk away. Australia have an early breakthrough and Sri Lanka look in trouble.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Mitchell Swepson

Commentary.Commentary: Short and turning away, Nissanka cuts it off the backfoot and Head at covers dives to his left to stop it.
This is on off, Pathum Nissanka drives it towards covers for a brace.
On midde this time, Pathum Nissanka defends it back towards the bowler.
Tosses it on middle with a hint of turn, Pathum Nissanka looks to play at it but misses.
This one lands outside off shaping it into the batter, Kusal Mendis goes on his backfoot and defends it away.
Goes fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis blocks it back towards the bowler.
Nathan Lyon bowls it outside off, Kusal Mendis defends it solidly off the front foot.
Kusal Mendis comes in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! This one lands on middle and fuller with some turn, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to sweep it but gets a slight bottom edge and gets towards the keeper who takes a sharp catch. The skipper departs at 23 and Australia get an early breakthrough.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: This one lands outside off shaping it away, Dimuth Karunaratne lets it go.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Pathum Nissanka guides it to deep extra covers where Nathan Lyon makes a diving stop at the boundary line. A couple of runs taken.
Goes on leg this time, Dimuth Karunaratne sweeps it towards backward square leg for one.
Goes on middle and fuller in length, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it back towards the bowler. Oh, its a no ball.
Bowls it on off, Pathum Nissanka pushes it towards mid on for one.
Fuller again and on off, Pathum Nissanka drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Goes fuller and down the middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up on middle, this is guided towards the leg side for one.
Mitchell Swepson comes into the attack.
It has been a great start for Sri Lanka so far. They are scoring at a run rate of around 7.50, that is incredible.
This one lands fuller with some turn, Dimuth Karunaratne gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Goes on off again, Dimuth Karunaratne eases it towards the off side.

Dimuth Karunaratne, the skipper of Sri Lanka says that it is very disappointing as the play got over in three days. Mentions that the Australian batters did really well and as a batting unit they need to play better and put pressure on bowlers. Further says that with the young bowling attack they need to do better and do the job. Mentions that it is not easy to bat against Nathan Lyon and they made some bad decisions in the game.

Pat Cummins, the victorious skipper is in for a chat. He starts by saying it was an amazing win. Mentions, he could not believe the game eneded so quickly. Adds the bravery and the proactiveness shown by the batters has been outstanding over this match. Says, Green has been a whacker, and he has found it in his first knock. He proved to be the difference in the end.

Cameron Green wins the Player of the Match award for his incredible effort with the blade. Green says there are a few experienced guys in the camp and that helped him a lot. He aimed to be proactive and thought of playing some shots regularly to keep the pressure off him.

Earlier in the match, after winning the toss and electing to bat first! Sri Lanka were off to a decent start but once the spinners were introduced, the wickets started to fall. Nathan Lyon was in action and showed his class along with Swepson. They didn't allow the score to flow quickly and bundled out Sri Lanka for 212. Lyon ended with a five-fer while his companion finished with three wickets. In reply, it was Usman Khawaja first and then Cameron Green in the lower order along with Alex Carey, they played out what proved to be a match-winning innings and got a handy lead of more than 100. Australia were aware of the spin-friendly pitch and introduced Lyon again quickly after Starc's spell in the start which didn't work out. The magician was at work again with his crime partner and with Travis Head joining them. Australia ripped apart the Lankan lineup. In the end, Australia won without breaking much sweat.

So, Day 3 is called the moving day but it turns out to be the result day as well. Australia were batting at the start of the day and inside one session, we have seen a whole innings wipe away, thanks to some exception bowling spell from the Aussie spinners. Quality over quantity! This was proven in this match. Sri Lanka had more spinners but it was the experience and quality of Australia that has helped them take the lead. Lyon, Swepson and Head stuck to their plans throughout the process to bundle Sri Lanka below-par score and then, Australia needed just one over to get over the victory line.

Well, the outcome was inevitable. A comprehensive win for Australia. A clinical display from them and they take the lead in this two-match Test series. Smiles everywhere in the Aussie camp as Warner hits the winning runs and fist pumps in the air. Cummins has a big smile on his face. What a win this is for the visitors!
